1477661382.m_KeyValue: ""When selecting a Catalyst, be sure to pay attention to its Aspect. I recommend selecting the same Aspect whenever possible.""

1480197567.m_KeyValue: "Her final song woven with the cheers: 'Congratulations on slaying the siren!'"

1480197569.m_KeyValue: ""I have one last question for you, Mistbound Terror.""

1480197570.m_KeyValue: ""The power of Black Blood lingers in the Siren's Tear, resonating within you day after day.""

1488904149.m_KeyValue: ""The key was discovered by the heirs of the three major families, who were then young apprentices in the Church. Little did they know how their destinies would unfold, or the twists that awaited them.""

1488904150.m_KeyValue: ""'You're not scared, are you?' Gilrain smirked as he strode past his friend without looking back. 'It's just a twig.'""

1488904151.m_KeyValue: ""'Click.' As the sound of the turning lock echoed and faded, a cabin—isolated from both the world and time—unveiled itself before the trio.""

1488904152.m_KeyValue: ""The three of them sat before the fireplace, poring over the cabin's notes in the flickering light.""

1488904153.m_KeyValue: "'It appears this Nikola is no longer alive.'"

1488904154.m_KeyValue: ""Indeed, but what exactly feels amiss? At times, one must tread carefully, mustn't they? After all, fate rarely offers a warning before we arrive at a crucial crossroads.""

1488907413.m_KeyValue: ""'It's rude to stare, meow...' With a casual flick of its tail, the scattered Tarot cards were swept cleanly back into a neat stack—How it managed that was anyone's guess.""

1488907414.m_KeyValue: ""With one hand gripping the crystal ball and the other casually dragging her inverted spear, Joan strode forward at an unhurried pace. The spear's tip scraped against the ground, causing a shrill sound of friction. Now and then, silver sparks arced from it, crackling through brittle leaves in her path.""

1488907415.m_KeyValue: ""A flick of the paw—A custom-made Tarot deck, a slightly worn crystal ball, and a matching velvet mat all flew neatly onto the long table nearby. 'There. Good enough, meow…'""

1488907416.m_KeyValue: ""With a fluid sweep of her lance, she unleashed a crackle of silver lightning that sliced through the thorny brush ahead. 'Nothing stands in the path of my lightning.'""

1488907417.m_KeyValue: ""As if she'd foreseen this outcome from the start, Joan reached out and picked up the crystal ball. 'Then we'll be taking this as our spoils of war.'""

1488907418.m_KeyValue: ""'So the Bell Ringer's card is The Death and my card is The Lovers... quite unexpected, meow.'""

1488907419.m_KeyValue: ""'I'll go first. In case it's a trap.' Without further comment, Theophane flipped over the card before him. The High Priestess.""

1488907424.m_KeyValue: ""Meanwhile, at the foot of the hill...""

1488974934.m_KeyValue: ""'The Carrelle family crest,' Agares muttered while crouching down. He ran his fingers across the gravestone, tracing the weathered grooves with the pads of his fingertips.""

1488974935.m_KeyValue: ""'Mm... what is it? I can't tell...' Without breaking composure, Noah took a subtle step back. 'More importantly... when's the last time you had a bath?'""

1488974936.m_KeyValue: ""Noticing Noah's puzzled expression, Agares pulled out a small folding spade from who-knows-where. 'We're digging up whatever's under!'""

1488974937.m_KeyValue: "'Oh...?' Even someone as averse to trouble as Twin Agares couldn't ignore that. A flicker of competitive fire lit in his eyes. 'Then let's put it to the test.'"

1488974938.m_KeyValue: "Someone else was here?! To think they went unnoticed by both Noah and Agares… Just who are they?!"

1488974939.m_KeyValue: ""'Heh. As expected of Noah Nevernight.' Moments later, a familiar voice echoed from within the mist. That belonged to none other than...""

1488974940.m_KeyValue: ""Wait, now that you mention it... that did happen! Twin Agares ties the score in a flash! It's neck and neck, and the match is heating up!""

1488974942.m_KeyValue: "'I think... it's a special kind of meteorite. Planted here by _$$that person_$$ to protect the Carrelle family.'"

1488976021.m_KeyValue: ""Acappella made a gesture of Covenant with her hands clasped together, trying to appear solemn. She would have... if not for her feet resting on a gravestone.""

1488976022.m_KeyValue: "'Step back! Your breathing is too loud—I'm trying to locate people by their heartbeats.'"

1488976027.m_KeyValue: "The new friend here seemed rather displeased with this title."

1488976028.m_KeyValue: "'You can speak? But how are you still alive?'"

1488976032.m_KeyValue: ""If one had to call it a cake... well, it was certainly something only Acappella could have created.""

1489047893.m_KeyValue: ""Clive paled. At that time, his birth parents were still alive, and he hadn't yet been adopted by his current father.""

1489047897.m_KeyValue: ""Hati craned her neck to gaze at the towering watchtower. Atop it stood a vigilant clan member, eyes fixed intently on the distant lands of the Bathorys.""

1489047898.m_KeyValue: ""Yet, as if by some inexplicable twist of fate, Gadric suddenly lost his footing. With a startled 'Ow,' he tumbled to the ground just inches from the water.""

1489047899.m_KeyValue: ""'I think I just tripped over my own foot,' Gadric said, once again attempting to scratch his head through his helmet in embarrassment.""

1489047900.m_KeyValue: ""Clive suddenly bristled with anger. With a dismissive 'Hmph,' he turned and strode towards the Fangtooth Tower. His father was just a stranger to him, and Clive couldn't care less about the man's strength.""

1489051160.m_KeyValue: ""'Atop the tower's summit, the moons blushed crimson one by one, then faded, and finally vanished. Meanwhile, the bodies of fallen Bloodborn accumulated, blanketing the pinnacle in a grim shroud.'""

1489051161.m_KeyValue: "'That's impossible!' Hati cried out. 'The Ganelons are the epitome of loyalty!'"

1489051162.m_KeyValue: ""'Heh heh,' Hati chuckled nervously, her discomfort evident.""

1489051164.m_KeyValue: ""As she stood alone atop the tower, swinging a borrowed greatsword, it suddenly dawned on her—she simply didn't possess her brother's natural talent for swordsmanship.""

1489079477.m_KeyValue: ""'Since there are no books here, we should take our leave,' said Piera. The eldest in the group was always aware of the dangers at stake.""

1489079478.m_KeyValue: ""'Look at these ruins around you. Faith collapsed here long ago,' Cain retorted. 'How can one blaspheme against what no longer exists?'""

1489079479.m_KeyValue: ""Piera, the senior disciple with the most battlefield experience, had already pinpointed the source of the strange feeling. 'Over there! Everyone, be on guard!'""

1489079480.m_KeyValue: ""But the Crescent Garden proved a bitter disappointment. The church lay in ruins, its crumbling walls suffocated by an unyielding embrace of rose vines.""

1489079483.m_KeyValue: ""'With no one from his family to support him, he became both an apostate and a betrayer of his family.'""

1489079484.m_KeyValue: ""'His wish was granted. He had a son who grew at an astonishing rate, becoming the most formidable warrior the land had ever seen.'""

1489080438.m_KeyValue: "'Yeah… there it is again. That dreadful little tingle—that's the feeling of someone talking behind our backs.'"

1489080439.m_KeyValue: ""At this very moment, Darcias was back at the Church, undergoing a full analysis of the mushroom's composition. The culprit, of course, had already forgotten the whole thing.""

1489080440.m_KeyValue: ""'Doesn't it look familiar?' With a quick motion, Thibault reached forward, drawing the others' attention to her hand. 'It resembles…'""

1489080441.m_KeyValue: ""So… the suited, numbered cards represent figures from each faction, while the others—those without suits or numbers—represent different abilities?""

1489080442.m_KeyValue: "'Tch… pulling something that troublesome right out the gate… Did that last move already cost me 500 life points?'"

1489080443.m_KeyValue: ""This deck of mine is better suited for attrition. Laying down key effects early on is crucial for controlling the pace… and I must admit, I don't mind this style of play.'""

1489080444.m_KeyValue: ""'But it's a gamble. A Covenant amplifies offensive power dramatically—but at the cost of resources. If she overextends, it could open her up to a counterattack.'""

1489080445.m_KeyValue: ""...Wahahaha! Agares, you'd better go get that back checked—this match is mine!' Acappella swept her gaze around the battlefield with a grin. 'Summon servant—Darcias!'""

1489080446.m_KeyValue: ""'Still, that weird deck was kind of fun. Let's bring it back to the Church for further study.' As she spoke, Acappella bent down to pick up the deck, which only Bell Ringers could see.""

1489119767.m_KeyValue: ""Edina gazed sorrowfully at the butterfly in her palm. Her master extended a branch to offer her a cup of tea, but all he received was a roll of the eyes from his disciple.""

1489119768.m_KeyValue: ""Edina gently raised the butterfly with broken wings again: 'Master, how do you suppose it managed to fly to this area?'""

1489119769.m_KeyValue: ""'Initially, the foreman harbored no lofty ideals; he simply needed the money and had no choice but to accept this job.'""

1489119770.m_KeyValue: ""'But just as they began their journey, they were struck by a massive blizzard. Suddenly, they faced a grim reality: pressing on meant almost certain death for everyone in those merciless snowy plains.'""

1489119771.m_KeyValue: ""Edina cupped her hands, sheltering and warming the delicate creature within, while scanning the snow-blanketed slopes for suitable plants.""

1489119772.m_KeyValue: ""'Even if we heal it, it cannot escape this snowy plain. The outcome of death is unchangeable.'""

1489151349.m_KeyValue: ""'Indeed we did, but the Wolf Family's Harvest Festival was more like a sporting event. I always took first place in the running races. Clive Jr., though, would insist he'd beat me when he grew up.'""

1489151350.m_KeyValue: ""With eyes closed, the girls could almost hear the creaking of a ship's mast. Only upon opening their eyes did the illusion dissolve, revealing the true source: the turning of the windmill's blades.""

1489151353.m_KeyValue: ""'I-I couldn't care less about the history of you stupid wolves!' Empousa stammered, her cheeks flushed with a mix of embarrassment and defiance.""

1489151354.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey, you dumb mutt, don't tell me you brought the wrong key?' Empousa's sharp words instantly shattered the melancholy that had been welling up in Hati's heart.""

1489151355.m_KeyValue: ""'Based on my understanding, fabricating such a story wouldn't benefit anyone. At most, it would only serve to strain relations between the Ganelon family, the Church, and other families.'""

1489151356.m_KeyValue: ""'Why?' Empousa exclaimed, even more astonished than Hati had been when her father first recounted this tale. 'Was this before the Bathorys began their research into immortality?'""

1489156661.m_KeyValue: "But when would the skies rumble with thunder once more?"

1489156663.m_KeyValue: "'Found it.' Hati pranced back like a cat while trying to brush the grime off her newfound treasure."

1489156664.m_KeyValue: ""Hati lowered her head, hugging the gloves. 'It's because my father said everyone's first pair of boxing gloves should be thrown into the sky, to send a challenge to the highest power.'""

1489156665.m_KeyValue: ""'Looks like rain's on its way,' Ressa observed, voicing the unwelcome truth no one wanted to hear. On the bright side, they had managed to complete the harvest just in time.""

1489156666.m_KeyValue: ""'To erect this new tower, he not only spent vast fortunes but also poured every ounce of his ingenuity into its design. The tower soared to unprecedented heights.'""

1489156667.m_KeyValue: ""'Why won't she hang out with us?' Empousa grumbled, contemplating ways to drag Ami out of the Bathory castle.""

1489156668.m_KeyValue: ""'I want to climb to the top of the mill tonight,' Hati revealed. 'There's something I need to find up there.'""

1489223221.m_KeyValue: ""'Wow, so this is what a hot spring feels like... My fatigue just melted away! This hot spring is incredible!'""

1489223222.m_KeyValue: ""'Why don't we flip a coin?' Ami chimed in eagerly, already holding one up.""

1489223224.m_KeyValue: "'So you're preaching about fairness while planning to pull rank as the Bell Ringer (Beast) to overrule us?'"

1489223225.m_KeyValue: "'Looks like there's only one way to settle this. We'll draw lots to decide who goes first.' Ami rummaged through her bag and pulled out a coin."

1489223227.m_KeyValue: ""'Hm? Could he be here of all places...' Noah mused as he dispersed the thin mist, revealing a peculiar sight—someone else was already in the very pool where Hati had fallen!""

1489223228.m_KeyValue: ""'At times like this, I find myself missing the crowded warmth of company,' Noah mused, raising a hand toward the glowing moon above, as if to grasp it. 'Perhaps sharing a hot spring with everyone wouldn't be so bad after all.'""

1489224181.m_KeyValue: "What a masterful setup. As expected of one of the most skilled bards in all of Minexus!"

1489224182.m_KeyValue: ""'Mercury can't melt human flesh...' Nicole turned the empty helmet over in her hands, as if weighing a new thought. '...but that only applies if what's beneath the armor is human.'""

1489224183.m_KeyValue: ""'Does that really sound plausible?' Nicole followed behind at a measured pace, her gaze narrowing into the mist where the voice had come from.""

1489224184.m_KeyValue: ""'That's impossible...' She scanned their surroundings, eyes searching through the mist-laced forest. 'If he'd done anything, the mist would've caught it.'""

1489224185.m_KeyValue: ""Before Gadric could finish, a sudden splash echoed through the steam. A new figure appeared in the spring beside him—could this be the _$$unexpected guest_$$ he was just about to mention?""

1489224186.m_KeyValue: ""'Ah, if you're asking about that...' Gadric let out a quiet sigh of relief. Clearly, being overheard talking to himself just now had unsettled him more than the idea of exposing his face.""

1489224187.m_KeyValue: ""'Huh? Where did he go...' Nicole stood up in the hot spring, turning to scan the mist for any sign of Gadric. Droplets slid down her body, vanishing into the thick mist.""

1489224188.m_KeyValue: ""'N-No... something's wrong... I can't...' Before he could finish, his vision blurred. Darkness swallowed the edges of his vision... and then everything.""

1489224193.m_KeyValue: "'Who knows. Maybe this thing holds a clue.' Darcias picked up the alchemical device..."

1489224194.m_KeyValue: ""Hold on. With the excess weeds cleared by Halfway to the Underworld, a second, strangely familiar figure was revealed crouching in the vegetable patch. Is that... another Gadric?""

1489295101.m_KeyValue: ""Ignoring the chatter of the other three, Goldland plonked himself down right where he stood. 'My magnificent golden body is upside down like a topsy-turvy turnip! This is absolutely, positively not beautiful! I simply cannot tolerate such an affront to aesthetics!'""

1489295102.m_KeyValue: ""Suddenly, the breeze fell silent. In that split second, one man seized his moment to act!""

1489295103.m_KeyValue: ""Van Helsing lapsed into silence. After a moment, he picked up the golden fishing rod and walked away, but not before leaving them with one last declaration: 'Never underestimate a man's determination!'""

1489295105.m_KeyValue: ""'...Wait, what? I'm paying rent? But I'm Empousa's...' Noah trailed off, then frowned. 'Hold on, why is Bella collecting rent anyway? Isn't this Bathory's castle?'""

1489295106.m_KeyValue: "'The competition is utterly irrelevant! The pearl that the Church seeks is hidden in this very fishing village. That's why I'm really here! And if my guess is correct—'"

1489295107.m_KeyValue: "Cain was about to agree when he caught Noah's subtle movement. 'Sure thing—wait a second. Hand over that Seafood Tycoon Pearl you're hiding first!'"

1489295108.m_KeyValue: "'Power without effort? Such a convenient thing doesn't exist in this world.' Noah's stern gaze made the others look away in shame."

1489297271.m_KeyValue: "'Ladies and gentlemen!' Acappella threw her hands up excitedly. 'Let the first-ever Sandy Fish-skin Ball Championship begin!'"

1489297272.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh my, this is getting interesting!' Acappella clapped her hands and turned to Lamia excitedly. 'I'm finally starting to look forward to this game.'""

1489297277.m_KeyValue: ""'Save your excuses!' Lamia violently waved her hand to cut off Tris. 'If it weren't for the Church, the Bathory family wouldn't have...' Her voice trailed off.""

1489297278.m_KeyValue: "'Huh? I didn't do anything!' Empousa jumped out. 'Don't let her size fool you—she's a genuine Bell Ringer from the Church!'"

1489297279.m_KeyValue: ""'Tch, look who's dawdling now...' Lamia followed Empousa toward the castle gates. 'But... what's the point of going to that wretched fishing village anyway?'""

1489297280.m_KeyValue: ""Before she could finish her thought, Acappella's voice suddenly rang out from behind her. 'My, my, what gossip is our Commander spreading now?'""

1489297281.m_KeyValue: ""'So it should be something like this...' Empousa took the fish-skin ball from Acappella, tossed it into the air, and as it fell, she hit it upward. 'One...'""

1489297282.m_KeyValue: ""'The first rule is simple: you score a point by landing the ball in the opponent's court. If it goes out of bounds, the point goes to the other team.'""

1489297283.m_KeyValue: "'Ta-da! It's done—a ball made of fish skin!' Acappella took the ball from Tris's hands and gave it a test bounce into the air."

1489300413.m_KeyValue: ""'You really don't let things go, do you?'""

1489300414.m_KeyValue: "'A race needs a prize. How about… the winner gets to ask the loser one question?'"

1489300415.m_KeyValue: ""Of course, sometimes a man does just want to watch the sea.""

1489300416.m_KeyValue: "An unexpected voice cut off Noah's communion with the sea."

1489300417.m_KeyValue: ""'I feel the same, though I'd enjoy it more if I won next time.'""

1489300419.m_KeyValue: ""And right out the gate, Agares surged ahead—pulling half a body's length in front of Noah!""

1489300420.m_KeyValue: "'Huh? And just where did you come from?'"

1489302585.m_KeyValue: "'Ah...!' Lamia immediately picked up the parchment. 'This is...'"

1489302589.m_KeyValue: ""With a sweep of her hands, Empousa commanded crimson flowers to surge across the court toward the opposite side of the net, spreading like a red carpet. 'Now, go—!'""

1489302591.m_KeyValue: ""'You might not be so lucky next time.' Though Tris delivered these words with a smile, they sent chills down everyone's spine.""

1489302592.m_KeyValue: ""Unusually, Lamia didn't argue back. '...Let's not dwell on this. There are more pressing matters at hand.'""

1489302593.m_KeyValue: ""As if by chance, the moment the seabird landed, a fierce look sparked in the eyes of those standing on either side of the nets—the unmistakable stance of those ready for competition.""

1489302594.m_KeyValue: ""'So... what shall we do about this, Acappella?' Tris turned to Acappella with a smile, seemingly unconcerned about the rapidly approaching fish-skin ball.""

1489302595.m_KeyValue: ""Tris nodded with a smile before lightning suddenly crackled across her body. She leaped gracefully—and in a flash, accompanied by rolling thunder, she vanished from where she stood.""

1489302596.m_KeyValue: ""Just as Lamia struck, Acappella extended one hand toward the ball, fingers positioned like a gun. 'Now bounce back!'""

1490754692.m_KeyValue: "Could there be more to this than just the contest? Hati's mind raced with speculation."

1490754693.m_KeyValue: ""'He didn't tell you anything about it?' Gadric asked, his chewing coming to an abrupt halt.""

1490754694.m_KeyValue: ""'Could it be that our father won?' Hati reasoned that since he mentioned it in front of them, the chances of her father winning must be quite high.""

1494098949.m_KeyValue: ""'On second thought, forget it,' Empousa said, waving her hand dismissively. 'I couldn't care less about all that war stuff anyway.'""

1494098950.m_KeyValue: ""'Tell us! Tell us!' Hati suddenly leaned in, then realized this matter wasn't as glorious as Empousa had made it out to be.""

1494098951.m_KeyValue: "Jestel let out a heavy sigh. 'But the Ganelon family is no more. We can't allow that chapter of history to simply fade into oblivion.'"

1494434121.m_KeyValue: ""That's not pilling, they're sequins. I guess you can't tell the difference.""

1494434154.m_KeyValue: ""(Sigh)... I'll consider this fan service. It's part of an idol's duties, after all.""

1494434187.m_KeyValue: "Idols must maintain proper distance from their audience. We can't break the rules."

1494434220.m_KeyValue: ""Acappella's handshake event is about to begin! Fans with numbered tickets, please line up here!""

1494434319.m_KeyValue: ""Don't touch anything, or you'll regret messing with my stage.""

1494434352.m_KeyValue: ""This song is filled with all sorts of emotions. What kind, you ask— I'm not telling!""

1496419660.m_KeyValue: ""One of the Bloodborn's surviving elders, also the youngest one. He seems to have some connection to the Cidhall family.""

1496419687.m_KeyValue: ""Clive's son, and sibling to Hati, currently traversing his defiant phase.""

1496640993.m_KeyValue: "Collect all memory fragments to receive rewards."

1500709018.m_KeyValue: ""Thanks to you, Acappella can now start a new life with the other children in the choir.""

1500709019.m_KeyValue: "Acappella's adoption papers... the Church approved it?"

1500709020.m_KeyValue: ""The choir takes these children in, and as the Commander, I naturally bear the responsibility of raising them.""

1500709021.m_KeyValue: "Now I see why you call them 'children.'"

1500709022.m_KeyValue: ""At Tris's invitation, I attended the hymn recital at the church. Acappella, that young girl, proved to be truly gifted—her performance was met with thunderous applause.""

1500709025.m_KeyValue: ""After the performance, Tris approached me with a smile, her eyes sparkling with joy.""

1500709030.m_KeyValue: ""As I executed more heretics, I came to realize that most of their children were innocent... A child shouldn't suffer for their parents' sins.""

1500709031.m_KeyValue: "It all began with a moment of mercy during a heretic's execution—that's when I brought Anna back with me."

During the fall of the celestial realm, they single-handedly rescued Gods trapped in the Nether Void and bravely vanquished any form of threat, thus becoming the scout and guardian of the celestial realm in one fell swoop. Those under the protection of this Celestial God are endowed with a fearless spirit.""

1506731805.m_KeyValue: ""You also call me 'Moonblessed'... But what you just said, do you mean Empousa is in some kind of trouble?""

1510933846.m_KeyValue:
""In Bella's secret treasure spot, there lies an inscribed pearl.

The pearl bears an inscription in human language, stating that Bella and Lorelei are friends for life.

When Lorelei's mother married Uncle Averdin, she received a pearl ring. The priest said that vows spoken over a pearl ring must never be broken.

Bella too made a vow to the pearl. And she will treasure it always.

This is her 'most unique birthday gift.'""

1510933912.m_KeyValue:
""For a long time after, no song came from the Siren's Tear. Then one day, I accidentally spilled wine on it—the pooled surface shimmered with a vision:

A maiden held a letter from the north, pressed close to her heart.

It spoke of the biting chill of those distant lands, so unlike the warm summers of Sapphire Isle; Of dry mornings with wind carrying grains of sand; Of being well—her moments of awakening growing longer.

She had read the letter countless times, clinging to it through long days of captivity and pain, holding fast to the hope of reunion.""

1511770940.m_KeyValue: "Allow me to join you in your future battles."

1511770941.m_KeyValue: ""Black Blood is still stirring within you, be careful!""

1515635448.m_KeyValue: "Don't come crying to me when you get into trouble!"

1515636603.m_KeyValue: "How many more tragedies born of ignorance must we witness..."

1515638781.m_KeyValue: ""You never fail to surprise me, like that unexpected move in chess. I must say, I quite enjoy it...""

1525072417.m_KeyValue: ""Sensing the overwhelming threat, Piera immediately signaled the others to retreat.""

1525072418.m_KeyValue: ""Van Helsing and Nicole began to retreat, as cautiously as when they had come.""

1525072419.m_KeyValue: ""However, they discovered that everything around them began to distort, while their own bodies seemed to grow and shrink erratically.""

1526332322.m_KeyValue: ""Without warning, Agares winced exaggeratedly and pressed a hand to his lower back. 'Ah… my old injury's acting up again. I'll need a proper soak in the hot springs to recover…'""

1526531239.m_KeyValue: ""Gains {0} Lifesteal. While Blood Moon is active, DMG dealt increases by {1}.""

1526934647.m_KeyValue: ""Could this be the grace of fate, allowing me to meet Miss Aiona, the 'Moonblessed', here and even earn her praise!""

1526934845.m_KeyValue: "These are Lady Empousa's Blood Servants. They must have sensed we were in danger and came to assist."

1527998892.m_KeyValue: ""As instructed, I visited Bella the moment I returned from Sapphire Isle.""

1527998894.m_KeyValue: "We could also pretend none of this ever happened."

1531331304.m_KeyValue: ""Damn it. I hate to say it, but I agree.""

1531331366.m_KeyValue:
""Slade gloated at me.
The person I saved that night had betrayed me. Slade promised that if she revealed my location, she would be granted freedom.""

1531331397.m_KeyValue:
""The full moon drifted slowly across the night sky, its luminance shifting with time.
The harsh moonlight exposed my wounds, revealing a fatal injury.
I broke into laughter.""

1533535696.m_KeyValue: ""The Black Blood has transformed William into a beast driven purely by desire. Timidity and self-doubt are stripped away. Ranna is beckoning to him — and there, where the claws of fear can never reach, lies only the promise of eternal peace.""

1536551097.m_KeyValue: "Can you guess which words of yours made me change my mind?"

1536556346.m_KeyValue: ""Bella: Alright, I shall trust your judgment this time.""

1536558260.m_KeyValue: ""Alright, since they're saying you're one of the Moonblessed, I suppose I'll trust you this time!""

1536561459.m_KeyValue: ""Fine, I guess you have a point there.""

1536562352.m_KeyValue: "Is it still possible to change my mind?"

1536563373.m_KeyValue: ""I must admit, your argument has finally convinced me.""

1536565551.m_KeyValue: "It's nothing. I just wanted to see your smile."

1536568622.m_KeyValue: ""Upon consideration, your choice is indeed the more prudent course of action.""

1537600504.m_KeyValue: ""Elite Knights who guard Sunset Isle. Unfortunately they have already began to crystallize. However, they hold fast to their posts, carrying out the orders of the Church in the last moments of their lives.""

1537600592.m_KeyValue: ""The current Gravekeeper of the Ganelon lineage, he lost his sanity and underwent mutation due to the spread of the Black Blood. He awaits in silence for the designated one's arrival.""

1537600593.m_KeyValue: ""The eldest of the Bathory family, and armor to the arrogant and cruel Bloodborn. Despite his proud demeanor, he isn't immune to the ravages of time.""

1537600600.m_KeyValue: "The Heretic Hunters of the Church who stare death in the face. They know well that even their baptism before the crusade could not change their inevitable fate. Their chainmail clangs like a bell rung at their own funeral."

1537600601.m_KeyValue: ""The Heretic Hunters of the Church who stare death in the face. They know well that even their baptism before the crusade could not change their inevitable fate. Their choice is both a solemn vow, and a final tribute to their faith.""

1537600604.m_KeyValue: ""Byproduct of Baphomet's flesh intercision experiments, carrying the remnants of his victims' Spirits. They dutifully execute their order to defend the castle.""

1537600605.m_KeyValue: ""Byproduct of Baphomet's flesh intercision experiments, carrying the remnants of his victims' Spirits. They dutifully execute their order to repel the intruders.""

1537600607.m_KeyValue: "Jestel seems to know this person very well."

Like a massive piece of amber, the salt coffin perfectly preserves the remains within, seemingly rendering null the passage of time.""

<alpha=#80>The ancients once associated immortality with the crescent moon. As the crystals refined from Lunarite naturally form into a teardrop-shape, alchemists have named them 'Moon Tear.'""

1564133521.m_KeyValue: "Progress to Floor 040 in Tower of The Bloodborn - Desire."

1568881732.m_KeyValue: ""'Most people in this world are cunning. I wonder, did he perhaps conceal certain truths when recruiting workers?'""

1568881734.m_KeyValue: ""'But plants do not deceive. In this vast snowy expanse, lies will inevitably be scattered by the relentless winds.'""

1568881735.m_KeyValue: ""'While evil does exist in this world, I firmly believe that the majority are good at heart. Just like plants... some are poisonous while others can cure ailments.'""

1569574283.m_KeyValue: ""It fits heavy equipment, offering outstanding survival.""

1575905453.m_KeyValue: ""Of course! Who do you think I am... Wait, why am I even taking orders from you!?""

1578006552.m_KeyValue: ""A junior monk of the Tempus Church, tasked with meting out punishment to those deviating from the Church's precepts. Their methods are notoriously brutal, often surpassing those deployed against heretics.""

1580600814.m_KeyValue: ""Without another word, Empousa dragged the other two out the door and made straight for Eye of God.""

1580600815.m_KeyValue: ""To my astonishment, I discovered that all we had been taught about it… was wrong.""

1580600816.m_KeyValue: ""'Aiona's studied astronomy since she was a child. When it comes to stargazing, few can match her.'""

1580600817.m_KeyValue: "Aiona let out a troubled sigh. 'There's been no real progress.'"

1580600818.m_KeyValue: ""'You could carry on her work. As long as someone continues her research, she won't be forgotten.'""

1580600820.m_KeyValue: ""Taking the previous journal pages in hand, Empousa began her own investigation.""

1580600821.m_KeyValue: "'Here—this looks like a letter from the author's friend.'"

1580601902.m_KeyValue: ""'_$$This is a calculated and theorized trajectory of the moon's movement. It may not be entirely precise, but I shall continue refining it._$$'""

1580601903.m_KeyValue: ""It was a densely packed entry, meticulously charting the moon's shifting phases over the course of a year.""

1580601904.m_KeyValue: "'This? Seriously? That's hideous!' Empousa gave a look of disgust."

1580773966.m_KeyValue: ""'...Tch, if we start fighting in front of this con artist, who knows when we'll be forced to buy things we'd never need,' Gilrain grumbled, his brows furrowed.""

1580773967.m_KeyValue: ""As his laugh erupted like thunder, he swung his axe to point at Gilrain. 'I see now... your true objective in joining the Bathory family was me all along!'""

1580773968.m_KeyValue: ""The absence of memories is one of Gilrain's deepest sorrows. Whether due to an unspeakable secret or a necessary sacrifice, he has lost all recollection of his former human life.""

1580773969.m_KeyValue: ""If he truly is just an empty shell without a soul... how does he differ from the shattered, stained piles of armor strewn across any battlefield? Can we still view 'him' as an existence? And perhaps more importantly—""

1580773973.m_KeyValue: ""Now, now, we did say the cat's background would be 'a complete mystery,' right? So naturally, its real name must be kept a secret.""

1580774926.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey Gilrain, looks like you're not feeling too well. But I've got just the thing—the latest product from the Puppet Association!'""

1580774927.m_KeyValue: ""He may be one of the four great elders, but it was just a cat after all! For the Grand Elder to be frolicking with a cat during a meeting—how undignified!""

1580774928.m_KeyValue: ""It wasn't until Bella solemnly interjected that everyone was jolted back to the reality: 'Well... while I couldn't quite grasp everything that was said, it seems the old-timer is suggesting that today's meeting has come to an end.'""

1580774929.m_KeyValue: ""Bella followed in Gilrain's wake, her mind already racing with ideas about which wares to peddle.""

1580774930.m_KeyValue: ""With a respectful nod to Baphomet, Gilrain and Bella stepped out of the way. Taking the lead, Baphomet walked with his back to the others, a faint smile playing across his aged visage—""

1580813140.m_KeyValue: "How did you even manage to fall like that?"

1580813166.m_KeyValue: ""'Waaah?!' Selena gasped in awe at the intricate mechanism, eyes wide as saucers as she peered into the narrow gap.""

1580813167.m_KeyValue: "Selena confidently shook off Bella's (four) hands. 'Hurry up! Silver-haired's waiting for us!'"

1580813168.m_KeyValue: "'I never imagined Selena would love grilled octopus so much.' The sun was already slipping into the sea as they stepped out of the Infernal Kitchen."

1580813169.m_KeyValue: ""Selena placed her hands on the doll-like beauty's cheeks, pulling the corners of her mouth outward, then squishing them back in. 'Th-this is... is... the Breath of Life!'""

1580813170.m_KeyValue: "'He probably just needed to wipe his hands.'"

1580813171.m_KeyValue: ""After a moment, Selena's tone wavered. 'F-Fine! I swear I'll pay you, Bella! Even if I haven't a single Soli to my name right now... (sobbing)!'""

1580813172.m_KeyValue: ""'About that first destination...' Bella glanced over her shoulder. 'According to the plan, we were to sail south from the Harbor of Soughs and reach the Dekatres Archipelago in two days.'""

1580813173.m_KeyValue: ""'If your body temperature's too low, then... then we'll have no choice but to rely on... h-human... w-warmth...' At that, Selena's face flushed red—though whether it was the blazing sun or something else entirely, no one could say.""

1580813178.m_KeyValue: ""Avoiding Selena's eyes, Bella turned her head slightly—and with two of her free hands, began performing her own version of the 'Breath of Life' on Selena's face. '...All right, then. Master Cook... Selena.'""

1580813179.m_KeyValue: ""'Dream Recipe?!' Selena perked up instantly, twisting upright with octopus-like agility to snatch the parchment.""

1580814258.m_KeyValue: ""'Fine! This is neither a product of alchemy nor any known magic in this world. It is something... unknown,' Cain unwillingly admitted.""

1580814259.m_KeyValue: ""'Within them, you will see the ideal version of yourself, and be mesmerized with self-adoration. But soon, horrifying things will begin to unfold.'""

1580814260.m_KeyValue: ""A chilling, otherworldly laugh emanated from the portrait. 'What makes you think I wouldn't?'""

1580814261.m_KeyValue: ""Cain replied with a smirk, 'Taking time to appreciate the fine arts after work is a way to discover new inspirations.'""

1580845842.m_KeyValue: ""A hush fell over the group. They began to fidget and cast their eyes about, clearly disinterested in the topic. After all, they had rehashed similar issues countless times before.""

1580845843.m_KeyValue: ""'What business is it of ours, and what blood conflicts do other families get into?' Gilrain scoffed. 'Do we even have the power to stick our noses in?'""

1580845844.m_KeyValue: ""'Now, now, let's all calm down. A good merchant never wants to drive away a potential customer.'""

1580845845.m_KeyValue: ""Baphomet explains, 'The ancestral blood of the Roland family, the Horse, is equally elusive. They bury their dead wherever they please across the great plains.'""

1580917715.m_KeyValue: ""Inevitably, a battle erupted. No one knows how many Ancestors perished—perhaps even more than during the Crimson Inquisition. Quite the irony, wouldn't you say?'""

1580917716.m_KeyValue: ""Isaac asked urgently, 'Did any of those Ancestors leave the vault? And what became of the prisoners?'""

1580917717.m_KeyValue: ""'Should we kill him?' Selena whispered, her eyes on the drowsy guard as she quietly drew her crossbow.""

1580918670.m_KeyValue: ""Bella, Empousa, and Lorelei were standing in a circle in the room. Which means, of course, to Lorelei's right… was the one holding the candle on page 47—Bella.""

1580918671.m_KeyValue: ""'Bella? What… what are you waiting for? Hurry up and find another candle!' Trying her best to stay composed, Empousa reached blindly toward Bella in the darkness.""

1580918673.m_KeyValue: ""'Ah...!' Ami's presence suddenly sparked a realization. 'Ami, do you remember the path you took to get in here? Can you lead us out?'""

1580918674.m_KeyValue: "'And...' Bella turned to Empousa with a meaningful glance. 'I used your name when I made that deal.'"

1580918677.m_KeyValue: "'Bella! You can’t just go spouting nonsense like that and worry our guest!'"

""Hati has disappeared.

While searching for her, I learned that many alchemists were gathering in Mouret, seeking mushrooms rumored to cure the Black Blood disease. But if they reopened the sealed grounds, the Black Blood would spread once again.

Yet when I arrived at the forbidden area, besides the dead alchemists on the ground, there was another figure—

Hati, whom I hadn't seen in a long time, unconscious among the flowers outside the forbidden grounds.""

""Most people have fantasized about having the power of precognition, and I'm no exception. So when I received that letter, alongside disbelief, there was also a hint of joy at seeing such a fantasy become reality. When imagination becomes real, when you can know what's going to happen in the future—such allure is hard to resist.

Beyond matters of life and death, even taking seriously the incident about breaking Cain's wine bottle could have prevented the later _$$debt collection._$$ So regardless of whether what that version of me said was true or false, I wanted to give it a try.""

""I remember Cain saying that he had originally meant for Lamia to go to Starfall Valley that night.

Empousa happened to overhear his conversation with Lamia, and that's why she arrived there first.

At first, I thought it was just typical rivalry between heirs, until Aiona revealed another side of the story—

That night, Empousa passed by the study, expecting to hear them discuss the usual topics like Alchemy or prophecies.

Until the word _$$dangerous_$$ caught her ear, and she heard Cain ordering Lamia to rescue a silver-haired man alone.

Fearing she might lose another sister, she immediately picked some scarlet flowers from the castle's back garden and, under cover of night, silently left the city disguised as a flower girl.""

1819925506.m_KeyValue: ""Crows that soar above Starfall Valley. After being infected with Black Blood outside the sealed area, they become extremely voracious, leaving no living being untouched.""

1819925507.m_KeyValue: ""The Church's Inquisition flag-bearer and Agares' subordinate. For some reason, he follows the Grand Inquisitor on trips even during vacation.""

1819925508.m_KeyValue: ""The Church's Chamber of War Flag-bearer and subordinate to Joan, responsible for boosting morale.""

1819925509.m_KeyValue: ""Starfall Valley villagers. Wrongly condemned as heretics by Church soldiers, they now face a cruel sentence.""

1819925594.m_KeyValue: ""A junior sorcerer of the Tempus Church, entrusted with reciting the powerful spells from the hallowed scriptures. <color=#D63536>Capable of executing a lethal blow to clustered heretics</color>.""

1819925595.m_KeyValue: ""A junior priest of the Tempus Church, adept in the art of healing through prayer, <color=#D63536>yet unskilled in personal defense</color>.""

1819925602.m_KeyValue: ""A most loyal servant of the Bathory family once, now a stone guardian who silently upholds their oath. With a body of solid stone, they strike down intruders.""

1819925604.m_KeyValue: ""Common blood servants of the Bathory family, shadows in the night, loyal to heirs of the bloodline. The power of Black Blood allows them to keenly sense their masters' will.""

1819925605.m_KeyValue: ""A most loyal servant of the Bathory family once, now a stone guardian who silently upholds their oath. With a body of solid stone, they wield magic through arms of obsidian sheen.""

1819925606.m_KeyValue: ""A junior knight of the Tempus Church, clad in holy armor. <color=#D63536>Their faith grows more fervent with every swing of their swords</color>.""

1819925607.m_KeyValue: ""Common blood servants of the Bathory family, shadows in the night, loyal to heirs of the bloodline. Emitting lethal sound waves through the power of Black Blood, they are death itself.""

1819925608.m_KeyValue: ""An elite knight of the Tempus Church, adorned in radiant golden armor as a testament to their divine blessing. Such gear is reserved only for the most ardent believers.""

1819925609.m_KeyValue: ""A junior knight of the Church, clad in holy armor. With shields as steadfast as their faith, they are ready to repel any heretic.""

1823896926.m_KeyValue: "Gilrain's Ultimate summons 3 Raging Bulls and knocks back enemies in their way."

1823896927.m_KeyValue: "Hati enters Bloodthirst at the start of battle. Both the radius of her Ultimate and Spectral Wolf Trap are greatly increased."

1823896928.m_KeyValue: ""Spectral Gilrain's Ultimate can target any enemy on the field. Upon casting, Gilrain teleports behind the target and deals AoE DMG. If an enemy is eliminated, the skill can be cast again, and will target the farthest enemy. Each subsequent cast deals slightly reduced DMG, up to 3 additional times, upon which Gilrain returns to his original position. During his Ultimate, Gilrain deals DMG to all enemies along his path. Up to 5 Shadowy Apparitions can be present, who will also cast their Ultimate from their position at the same time as Gilrain.""

1823896929.m_KeyValue: ""Mass's Ultimate has an increased DMG radius. When enemies are eliminated, Mass recovers HP and gradually reduces the Bloodsoul cost of her next Ultimate.""

1823896930.m_KeyValue: ""Ressa's Ultimate now targets an enemy in range and pulls in surrounding enemies in a fan, dealing DMG to the target and Bounce DMG to surrounding enemies.""

1823896931.m_KeyValue: ""Darcias deals 50% increased DMG to enemies with Bloodthirst, and the radius of her Heavy Strike is greatly increased.""

1823896932.m_KeyValue: ""Friedrich's Ultimate radius is increased. Upon gaining a Shield, deals 60% of the Shield value (P. DMG) to nearby enemies.""

1823896933.m_KeyValue: "Theophane's Ultimate now creates a Flaming Barrier with a greatly increased area. Enemies near the Flaming Barrier continuously take DMG."

1825011036.m_KeyValue: ""Some bats forgotten by time and space, endlessly squabbling over food, carefree, like echoes of the newfound joy of Lamia, the _$$runaway._$$ In another life, would she ever miss those petty battles at home after breaking free?""

1825011037.m_KeyValue: ""A torch forgotten by time and space. Raising it was Agares's first act of feigned loyalty as _$$Dracula's follower._$$ In another life, where he stands but one step from godhood, would he ever reminisce about the Manor of Eternal Flame?""

1825011038.m_KeyValue: ""A gauntlet forgotten by time and space. The wolf claws on it were the prized weapons of Hati. In another life, no longer the _$$warrior of Ganelon,_$$ would she simply wear the cloak her father made and visit the town for the blooming Wolfsbane?""

1825011039.m_KeyValue: ""A sword forgotten by time and space, one that has purged countless heretics, bestowed upon Gilrain by the Church when he was chosen as the _$$Bell Ringer of Light._$$ In another life, no longer shying away from the light, would he secretly long for a worthy adversary?""

1825011040.m_KeyValue: ""A mantle forgotten by time and space. The massive bat wings are a symbol of loyalty to Dracula as a _$$Bloodborn elder._$$ In another life, would Mass move on from that palace after turning her back on the family?""

1825011041.m_KeyValue: ""Shears forgotten by time and space. In the hands of Gilrain, the _$$castle gardener,_$$ it became a tool for shearing sheep and tending to flowers. In another life, where peace is his sole pursuit, would he ever truly quench his hunger for power?""

1825011042.m_KeyValue: ""Remains of beasts forgotten by time and space. The precise cuts speak to the surgical mastery of the _$$bounty hunter_$$ Darcias. In another life, would she look back on her pursuit of wealth as a quiet submission to a darker power?""

1825011043.m_KeyValue: ""A pair of handwraps forgotten by time and space. The rose pattern adorning them symbolizes the happy ending of _$$village girl_$$ Ressa with her childhood sweetheart. In another life, would she ever realize how precious her simple life on Sunset Isle was?""

1825011044.m_KeyValue: ""Decorations forgotten by time and space. A shield-like statue bearing the crest of the deities, handpicked by the _$$humble dad_$$ Theophane as a gift for his beloved daughter. In another life, would he simply savor the joy of family in a world untouched by war?""

1825011045.m_KeyValue: ""A longsword forgotten by time and space. Its unique design marks it as belonging to the second son of the Roland family—the Knight. In another life, freed from his fate as a Bell Ringer candidate, would Friedrich ever find his true calling?""

1829504165.m_KeyValue: "Anna? What does she have to do with this?"

1835041285.m_KeyValue: "She said this issue stems from interpersonal connections."

1835041290.m_KeyValue: "I can see that smile on your face. Was the divination accurate?"

1835041291.m_KeyValue: ""Jacintha Dalcarlo, who happens to be here, stands outside a tent waiting for Noah to complete his divination inside.""

1835041292.m_KeyValue: ""In the outskirts of Bathory Castle at night, a spiritual gathering was taking place. People dressed in mysterious attire sat on the lawn around tents offering various services, including divination.""

1835041295.m_KeyValue: "She said I'm currently troubled by something that's been keeping me awake for a long time."

1839917543.m_KeyValue: ""What's this, some cheap shot to get under my skin? Nice try, but I couldn't care less.""

1839920744.m_KeyValue: ""Sigh, I really can't understand what those colleagues of mine find so interesting about you.""

1841705380.m_KeyValue: "Auto-battle will automatically unleash the Vassals' Ultimate."

1841705381.m_KeyValue: "Double Speed will speed up the battle."

1841705383.m_KeyValue: "The Auto-battle and Double Speed functions have been unlocked."

1841705386.m_KeyValue: ""If you feel tired of battling, you can activate the corresponding functions.""

1841705387.m_KeyValue: ""Just give us the instructions, and we will adapt our fighting strategy for you.""

1841705476.m_KeyValue: ""When deploying, be mindful of their movement paths. Be sure to position your Vassals so they can intercept them and protect the rear. Caution is advised!""

1841705477.m_KeyValue: "That's right. They are the most ferocious species of all the Blood Servants. They will charge mercilessly until stopped."

1841705478.m_KeyValue: "Are these bats... the same ones raised by Empousa?"

1841705479.m_KeyValue: ""When deploying, pay attention to their charging paths and position me at the front to protect the rear.""

1841705480.m_KeyValue: "I'll block it and ensure it doesn't threaten any of you."

1841705481.m_KeyValue: "They are the most ferocious among the Blood Servants raised by that young lady. They will charge with reckless abandon until they are stopped."

1841705482.m_KeyValue: "Seems like there are new variants we haven't encountered before."

1841705490.m_KeyValue: "Position them opposite of the enemy's ranged units to quickly attack their rear."

1841705491.m_KeyValue: "Our Blood Servants will also assist us to infiltrate the enemy's back line."

1844102078.m_KeyValue: ""Card skill that deals fixed AoE DMG in a select area. Initial energy cost is 8, but reduces by 1 for every 20 monsters eliminated, while increasing DMG.""

1845042337.m_KeyValue: ""The celestial dance of stars whispers the ebb and flow of fate, etching omens of things to come. Sages, with eyes turned skyward each night, unravel the tapestry of tomorrow.""

1845216191.m_KeyValue: ""A peculiar device prone to sudden explosions. In the wrong hands, the consequences are unthinkable.""

1845217214.m_KeyValue: ""A dark, bitter liquid that keeps one alert through the night. Would likely fetch a good price among night watchmen and ascetics.""

1845260993.m_KeyValue: ""Note that there are different types of mechanisms. Some only activate while standing on them, and deactivate as soon as you step off.""

1845389404.m_KeyValue: "A transparent sphere filled with liquid. Alchemists claim it holds the key to creating life—though some see it as the birth of Calamity."

1845389406.m_KeyValue: ""One of the three origins of Alchemy. This yellow mineral is extremely flammable, releasing an intense scent when burned. It never fails to stir an alchemist's imagination about souls.""

1845389407.m_KeyValue: ""A reddish-brown metal that lasts much longer than iron, though it is less durable than gold or silver. It retains its noble luster through the wear of time.""

1853417792.m_KeyValue: "That chilling silver hair and those inscrutable crimson eyes..."

1862951371.m_KeyValue: "Unlocks the Contest Winner's Frame. Can be changed in Profile Settings."

1867691615.m_KeyValue: ""'Why not put in some real effort and source your ingredients from the market in the neighboring town? And speaking of which, what kind of life have Empousa and the others been living? It's hard to believe they've never even tasted seafood.'""

1867691618.m_KeyValue: "Cain gave an elegant butler's bow and smiled lazily. 'I'm planning to introduce a new cuisine for tonight's dinner. The Bathory ladies have yet to experience the delights of seafood.'"

1868203872.m_KeyValue: "The timing is indeed propitious. You may proceed."

1868207073.m_KeyValue: "It aligns closely with our predetermined course."

1869276980.m_KeyValue: ""The castle curtains show signs of being gnawed by rats, occasionally allowing sunlight to penetrate. Some vassals have suggested replacing them with wool tapestries for better light blocking, improving everyone's living conditions and sleep quality. What are your thoughts on this?""

1869277077.m_KeyValue: ""A Vassal has returned from their travels and shared insights on the noble education practices within the Alita family. What lessons, if any, should we take from their methods?""

1869277244.m_KeyValue: "A senior Vassal has requested to enter the long sleep. This seems to be the first time a Vassal has voluntarily made such a choice. Should we grant their request?"

1869277310.m_KeyValue: ""We've received a letter from a vassal expressing that the castle's menu is rather monotonous. They suggest adding appetizers, desserts, and beverages in addition to the main course. What are your thoughts on this matter?""

1869277341.m_KeyValue: ""Our family has always adhered to a 'family-first policy' in all matters. In our dealings with outsiders, this often makes us appear somewhat inflexible. What are your views on this matter?""

1869277376.m_KeyValue: "Several Vassals have reported that the daily evening meetings are inefficient and disrupt their regular sleep. They propose we discontinue them entirely. What do you think of this suggestion?"

1869277407.m_KeyValue: ""Allegedly, the Western Kingdom is planning to attack the Howling Peninsula. Although the authenticity of this information has yet to be verified, we should remain vigilant. Perhaps it's time to consider cultivating some reliable intelligence-gathering personnel. Do you agree?""

1869277442.m_KeyValue: ""Recently, a vassal has been frequently attending meetings in bat form, which seems to have caused dissatisfaction among other attendees. What are your thoughts on allowing vassals to attend meetings in transformed states?""

1869277473.m_KeyValue: "A Vassal has reported that the castle library has a limited variety of books and suggested we purchase some new genres. What are your thoughts on this matter?"

1869277539.m_KeyValue: ""A vassal has secretly adopted a stray cat from near the castle. However, our family rules explicitly state that no pets other than Blood Servants are allowed. What are your thoughts on revoking this rule?""

1869281766.m_KeyValue:
""A vessel filled with blood. Use to exchange for Divine Blood Drops, based on your Moonlight Faith LV.
<alpha=#80>From the stars we were born, yet now we gaze at them from afar.""

1869281768.m_KeyValue:
""A box full of Soli. Use to exchange for Soli equal to the yield in the specific ritual time (based on Moonlight Faith level).
<alpha=#80>Even creatures of the night find solace in the allure of material riches.""

1869281769.m_KeyValue:
""A vessel full of Pure Blood Essence. Use to exchange for Pure Blood Essence equals to the yield in the specific ritual time (based on Moonlight Faith level).
<alpha=#80>Its deep crimson hues give onlookers an unsettling feeling.""

1870573392.m_KeyValue:
""Soul Shards collected by the undertaker. Collect 50 of them for a chance to obtain Church Vassals.
<alpha=#80>_$$All are born free, yet all are bound by the chains of order._$$""

1870573423.m_KeyValue:
""Soul Shards collected by the undertaker. Collect 50 of them to Embrace SR/SSR Vassals or above.
<alpha=#80>Notes from the undertaker's journal: _$$This soul persists yet, lingering in anticipation of divine guidance._$$""

1872094000.m_KeyValue: "Increases HP and P. DEF of Vassals with Heavy Equipment."

1873620834.m_KeyValue: "C-Cain!? You... Why are you with them?"

1873626050.m_KeyValue: "Someone in Priest Mira's team was injured. They said they'll catch up with us later."

1880115041.m_KeyValue: ""Do you even need to ask? It's our protagonist, of course!""

1884177818.m_KeyValue: ""Cooking destroys the essence of blood. Would you have us adopt the digestive sensibilities of humans? In my view, we should steadfastly maintain the Bloodborn tradition of consuming raw sustenance.""

1884177915.m_KeyValue: ""Besides, what good could possibly come from anything made by the Church? If you ask me, we'd be better off saving our money!""

1888245502.m_KeyValue:
""When all spirits are defeated and no Flaming Souls remain on the field, Baphomet begins charging, and after a period, deals strong P. DMG to enemies in a large area ahead. This skill can be interrupted by dealing sufficient DMG during his charging phase, which will weaken Baphomet.
While weakened, Baphomet loses his Soulless Armor and DMG Down effect, and DMG Taken will be greatly increased.""

1892188676.m_KeyValue: ""Finally, Aiona of the Alita family, masters of time itself. In a future beyond Aiona's vision, the fateful crossroads loom ever closer.""

1892188677.m_KeyValue: ""The three proceeded in silence through the mist. What sounded like the wailing of the dead emanated from the birch trees around them. The mist swirled like caressing shadows, enveloping them in a dreamlike state.""

1892188678.m_KeyValue: ""'This place must have belonged to a scholar,' Friedrich observed as he gently brushed away years of dust.""

1892188679.m_KeyValue: ""Predictably, Gilrain just rolled his eyes at Friedrich. But a moment later, he suddenly stood up.""

1892188680.m_KeyValue: ""'Father once spoke of a group of cartographers who crossed the continent, determined to map the world by the steps of their own feet,' recalled Friedrich as he took on a solemn expression.""

1892191940.m_KeyValue: ""As she spoke, she placed the crystal ball onto the cushion laid across the table. Whether it was her influence or something else… faint streaks of lightning began to flicker within the crystal's core.""

1892191941.m_KeyValue: ""'Don't intervene. This is my war.' With that, she halted before the tent, spear gripped firm, gaze locked onto the shadowy interior beyond the flap.""

1892191942.m_KeyValue: ""Wait, what about the crystal ball!? That's the main tool for fortune-telling, isn't it!?""

1892191943.m_KeyValue: "—or so claimed a suspicious flyer stuck to an even more suspicious travel tent."

1892191944.m_KeyValue: ""At some point, the black cat lounging on the cushion had vanished without a trace... Then, from the far end of the tent, a silhouette emerged.""

1892191945.m_KeyValue: "'Death is numbered thirteen. Lovers is only six. The outcome is clear.'"

1892191946.m_KeyValue: ""Knew you Bell Ringers wouldn't know anything about Tarot. There are now rules meow.' A flick of its tail, 'intepret it however you want, as long as your reading turns out accurate meow.'""

1892191947.m_KeyValue: ""Oh, come on! Why does the cat look so shaken!? And throwing in a half-hearted _$$meow_$$ now just feels sarcastic! There's no way that wasn't mockery, right?""

1892191951.m_KeyValue: "'The mission is complete. Why wouldn't we leave?' Joan shot Theophane a glance. 'Don't tell me you've already forgotten why we came to Eye of God.'"

1892259460.m_KeyValue: ""Noah followed Agares further in, his eyes scanning the overgrowth, noting the scattered gravestones along the path. 'A lot of these seem to belong to the Carrelle family...'""

1892259461.m_KeyValue: ""'Come now, no need to skulk around like some shy stray.' Without so much as a glance back, Agares waved a hand behind him and continued walking. As if expecting Noah to follow.""

1892259462.m_KeyValue: ""'Come on now, what's with that look...' Agares raised the black, unidentifiable stone in his hand and gestured toward Noah. 'The smell's coming from this.'""

1892259463.m_KeyValue: ""Agares never finished his sentence. At that moment, his spade struck something solid with a sharp clang—the unmistakable ring of metal against metal.""

1892259464.m_KeyValue: ""And yet, the two men stood unfazed by the chill, for they were agents of flame. In the name of the Bell Ringer, a battle unlike any other was about to begin!""

1892259465.m_KeyValue: ""That's right! The one struck by the black, unidentified stone Agares had just thrown... was none other than _$$Agares_$$!""

1892259466.m_KeyValue: ""'You're... Mass.' Noah glanced around, only to find the other Agares had vanished. 'Who's the other one?'""

1892259467.m_KeyValue: "*Note: This scene may be mildly unsettling. Sensitive viewers are advised not to let their imaginations run too wild."

1892259469.m_KeyValue: ""Mass left her words hanging, rising to her feet and gazing off into the distance—lost in her memories. Noah wisely chose not to press further.""

1892260548.m_KeyValue: ""Yes, she could hear heartbeats. And yes, she was just that exceptional.""

1892260549.m_KeyValue: ""Yes, this is the <style=""Highlight"">Wailing Crypts</style> of the Bathory family!! If you truly read the air!""

1892260550.m_KeyValue: ""'I can hear you, you know.' Darcias murmured, as she slid the key into the stone door's groove.""

1892260551.m_KeyValue: "'I never knew a Covenant could be used like that...'"

1892260553.m_KeyValue: ""'Ah, that one from before must be their lead singer.'""

1892260555.m_KeyValue: "'But today should be a day off!' Darcias pulled at Acappella's hat."

1892260559.m_KeyValue: ""'Uh, the 'cake' won't be necessary.' Darcias put away the 'cake,' crushing Acappella's dream of becoming a top chef.""

1892315160.m_KeyValue: ""Stay out of any Guards' line of sight during the heist. Being spotted will greatly increase their Alert level, and units will be sent to capture you.""

1892332420.m_KeyValue: ""'But as soon as we began the duel, I knew I'd made a mistake. We were in a forest, and your father, knowing I wouldn't harm small animals, quickly gained the upper hand.'""

1892332424.m_KeyValue: ""Clive brandished his short sword and lunged at Gadric, who merely sidestepped the attack with surprising grace for such a rotund figure.""

1892332425.m_KeyValue: ""Gadric found himself sprawled upon the slippery rocks, absently scratching his equally smooth helmet.""

1892332426.m_KeyValue: ""'The First Knight?' Uncle Gadric mused, looking up at the boy.""

1892332427.m_KeyValue: ""Hati unlocked the door at the base of the tower and retrieved a basket. Inside lay a hearty loaf of dark bread, a wedge of cheese, a cured ham, and a flask of wine.""

1892335687.m_KeyValue: ""'In the aftermath, it took the victorious army another month to erect a smaller Fangtooth Tower on the original site. This very tower endures to this day, standing as a silent witness to history.'""

1892335688.m_KeyValue: ""'The Aegis warriors hid behind massive shields, waiting for nightfall. They were determined to prevent anyone from escaping the tower.'""

1892335689.m_KeyValue: ""'You know about it too!' Empousa exclaimed, her face lighting up with delight.""

1892335690.m_KeyValue: ""'Yes, I've heard that too,' Empousa nodded. 'But unlike you, we can't control the wolf packs in Lupine Forest. This tower can only function as an early warning system at best.'""

1892335691.m_KeyValue: ""'This is my family's domain,' Empousa declared imperiously. 'As a guest, shouldn't you show some respect to your hosts?'""

1892364004.m_KeyValue: "'The goddess's repeated treachery against the Bathory family left them with no choice but to seek an alliance with Dracula.'"

1892364005.m_KeyValue: ""'We're leaving,' Piera cut in firmly. 'Our only purpose here is to find useful texts. Whatever he's doing is irrelevant to our mission.'""

1892364006.m_KeyValue: "'To use the power of time manipulation in a sacred place of the Church is utter blasphemy!' Isaac's shock quickly gave way to a surge of righteous fury."

1892364007.m_KeyValue: ""Nicole, the middle disciple, offered a contrasting view. 'Many of the Church's texts are safeguarded by special measures. They wouldn't succumb to decay so easily.'""

1892364010.m_KeyValue: ""Yet, as they departed Crescent Garden, they all found themselves pondering whether their master's true purpose in bringing them here was truly in pursuit of truth.""

1892364011.m_KeyValue: "'He was ready for the battlefield before he could even utter his first word.'"

1892364964.m_KeyValue: "'Sure am. What were you saying again?'"

1892364965.m_KeyValue: ""'Fine, fine! I'll come out—just stop tugging on my receiver!'""

1892364966.m_KeyValue: ""Thibault halted and turned toward the direction Acappella had pointed. 'Over there, you say…'""

1892364967.m_KeyValue: ""Aside from the Church's crest, there are three other distinct suits. Structurally, they do resemble Tarot cards.'""

1892364968.m_KeyValue: "'A treasure etched with the dreams of the entire continent… then how about Pocket Dreams?'"

1892364969.m_KeyValue: ""Agares held a (Bell Ringer–only) card between his index and middle finger. 'So… it's finally my turn. In that case, I—'""

1892364970.m_KeyValue: ""Tch, fine—if that's how it's gonna be…' Acappella drew a card from the top of the deck (Bell Ringer–only). 'Perfect timing! Alright, I'm playing this one!'""

1892364971.m_KeyValue: "That man… was he finally getting serious? Of course—becoming a Bell Ringer was never about luck."

1892364973.m_KeyValue: "...Wait. Everyone can see the cards now!? What—what is going on!?"

1892404294.m_KeyValue: ""'They were hit by another blizzard, but this time, he chose to leave the safety of the waystation behind. It was as if he was gambling with his very life, plunging into the howling storm towards his goal.'""

1892404295.m_KeyValue: ""'The eggs swiftly hatch into larvae, which voraciously feed to amass energy. They promptly pupate before emerging as fleeting adult butterflies, ready to continue their odyssey across the unforgiving snowy plains.'""

1892404296.m_KeyValue: ""Yggdrasill's branches and leaves stirred gently, as if contemplating the question with profound consideration.""

1892404297.m_KeyValue: ""Ah, I see. Edina just plucked a leaf from her master's branch and dropped it into some boiling water.""

1892404298.m_KeyValue: "'The life force a plant can absorb from the frozen earth is limited. Even restoring the life of a butterfly's could cost a shrub its life.'"

1892404299.m_KeyValue: ""'Master, have you heard the tale of the one who built this waystation?' Edina inquired after lighting the furnace.""

1892435876.m_KeyValue: "Hati glanced up at the windmill. 'The route goes from this windmill to the town gate and then back again!'"

1892435877.m_KeyValue: ""'The Ganelon family is extinct,' Hati replied, her bitter smile tinged with irony. 'How could there be any wolf packs left?'""

1892435880.m_KeyValue: ""'Desperate, the Ganelon family sought aid from major families across the continent, even appealing to the Church. But all turned them away, citing various reasons.'""

1892435881.m_KeyValue: ""'Does it really matter?' Ami's voice called from behind them. She had been wandering through the wheat fields, which explained her delayed arrival.""

1892435882.m_KeyValue: ""'I believe it's because the Ganelon family, having learned farming, expanded Mouret and increased its population. This led to them becoming a major force in the subsequent 'Crimson Inquisition'.'""

1892435883.m_KeyValue: ""Hati said, with evident reluctance, 'According to the explanation given by the Bathory family head at that time, they were concerned that if the Ganelon family became too weak, the Church might turn its attention directly to the Bathory family.'""

1892441190.m_KeyValue: "'Is that... a boxing glove?' Ressa recognized the object before Hati could explain."

1892441191.m_KeyValue: ""'Because father was lying. There's no such tradition in our family. I've been feigning ignorance this whole time, but now...'""

1892441192.m_KeyValue: ""'I didn't think a Bloodborn would be afraid of lightning,' Ressa said with a gentle, comforting smile.""

1892441193.m_KeyValue: ""'Curiously, the structure itself remained untouched, standing resolute for decades before it was finally dismantled.'""

1892441194.m_KeyValue: ""To protect farmers within the Bathory territory from wolf attacks during the harvest, Hati had been making daily trips to Mouret.""

1892441195.m_KeyValue: "'How hard is it?' Ressa asked with concern."

1892507748.m_KeyValue: ""Actually, Agares’s back had never been a problem—it was just an excuse he made up to get out of work.""

1892507749.m_KeyValue: ""Just as Noah was about to reveal story-changing truth again, a wild brown bear wandered by, casually dragging a trembling squirrel, and stepped into the hot spring...""

1892507750.m_KeyValue: ""'—and create the ultimate fatigue-relieving hot spring, this tiny sacrifice is completely worth it.'""

1892507751.m_KeyValue: ""'Isn't it a little too convenient that these sticks just happened to be here, and they're exactly three long and one short?'""

1892507752.m_KeyValue: ""'If it lands on either heads or tails, then I get to go first!'""

1892507753.m_KeyValue: ""'...Well, we should respect the proper order. Since Agares is already using the spring, we should look for another—'""

1892507754.m_KeyValue: "'This isn't something Noah can fix just by dropping to his knees and apologizing.'"

1892507755.m_KeyValue: ""'I get that good hot springs are... ugh... usually hidden away, but how much longer until we... urp—!'""

1892508708.m_KeyValue: ""But before we unveil the final answer, let's pause the tale for just a moment... and hear from our esteemed audience—What do you think lies beneath Gadric’s armor?""

1892508709.m_KeyValue: "'Or perhaps...' Nicole leaned in to peer inside the hollow shell of armor. '...the real question is whether Gadric ever had a body at all.'"

1892508710.m_KeyValue: ""'Obviously, to make him think we fell for this painfully obvious trap.'""

1892508711.m_KeyValue: ""Both Darcias and Nicole instinctively looked up—And in the next instant, the truth struck them.""

1892508712.m_KeyValue: "'Hmm? Why'd you stop?' Darcias looked at him expressionlessly. 'Don't mind me. Carry on.'"

1892508714.m_KeyValue: ""Take the infamous Church carriage incident—after a noble family's coach plunged off a cliff, the culprit, a young lady of high standing, confidently claimed she did it to save the man fated to become her Vassal.""

1892508715.m_KeyValue: ""As if in response to her voice, faint ripples spread across the surface. Then with a splash, Gadric's body rose from the depths.""

1892508720.m_KeyValue: ""Gadric, who was tending the garden, straightened up and gazed in the direction of Ethereal Springs. 'Ah, looks like another set of armor got scrapped.'""

1892508721.m_KeyValue: "So this was all Acappella's trap from the start... But seriously... Should a Bell Ringer really be spending their whole day doing stuff like this?"

1892579628.m_KeyValue: ""'Very well, let's use this interlude to clarify the competition rules,' Van Helsing glanced around. 'The competition will be team-based. The objective is simple: the team that catches the most fish within the time limit wins.'""

1892579629.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh? So this is...' Another elegant voice chimed in, barely concealing their curiosity and excitement.""

1892579630.m_KeyValue: ""'Why, you ask, did he have access to so much seafood? The answer is simple: smuggling, of course!'""

1892579631.m_KeyValue: "'That's the essence of teamwork. He fishes while I block. Using the rules to our advantage is part of the game. Blame your lack of competition experience!'"

1892579632.m_KeyValue: ""Van Helsing burst out of a dilapidated shack nearby, drawn by the commotion. As the dust began to settle, an utterly bizarre scene unfolded before him—one that would be seared into his memory for the rest of his days.""

1892579633.m_KeyValue: ""'...The Seafood Tycoon Pearl?' After hearing this mystical term from Cain, Noah could no longer contain his curiosity. 'Is this how Goldland dominated the seafood market?'""

1892579635.m_KeyValue: ""Seeing that everyone had settled down, Noah calmly addressed them, his tone measured and guiding. 'Let's end this foolishness and do something worthwhile.'""

1892581799.m_KeyValue: ""Before Empousa could finish, Tris's hand whipped through the air. A silver needle, crackling with lightning, shot past Empousa's face, slicing off a strand of her hair.""

1892581804.m_KeyValue: ""As tensions rose between the two sides... Tris suddenly stepped forward, positioning herself between the opposing groups with an outstretched hand.""

1892581805.m_KeyValue: "'...Why are you making such a big deal out of this?' Empousa covered her face in exasperation. 'Why do I have to deal with these people...'"

1892581806.m_KeyValue: ""'Shh, be quiet!' Sensing something, Lamia held out an arm to stop Empousa. The sisters quickly ducked into the shadows, staying on high alert.""

1892581807.m_KeyValue: ""The golden-haired woman smiled as she watched Acappella's figure enter the cabin, then turned her gaze back to where the sea met the sky. '...I hope no storm is brewing.'""

1892581809.m_KeyValue: "Eh?! The whole game is decided by a single point? That seems risky... Or does Tris have some secret winning strategy up her sleeve?"

1892581811.m_KeyValue: ""'Hmph, is this really the best that the Church's weapon and Bell Ringer can come up with?' Empousa shook her head lightly, mocking Tris's suggestion.""

1892584940.m_KeyValue: "It's best to keep distance from people who have a few screws loose. Noah made a point by putting some distance between them."

1892584941.m_KeyValue: ""A heated, high-stakes race is about to begin.""

1892584942.m_KeyValue: "'To sink beneath the sea… it's a wonderful experience.'"

1892584943.m_KeyValue: ""So much for Noah's hard-earned peace and quiet. Someone had come uninvited. Someone who bore fire, yet willingly approached the sea. Who could it possibly be—""

1892584944.m_KeyValue: "'It's not just the sea. Isn't that true for people too? Maybe all we can do… is learn to live with that complexity.'"

1892584946.m_KeyValue: ""To avoid them, Noah dove beneath the surface—Now only Agares could be seen above the water.""

1892584947.m_KeyValue: ""With the moonlight at their backs, the three walked toward the shore, the seawater trailing from their bodies leaving paths in the sand.""

1892587112.m_KeyValue: "'38 million Soli?!' Lamia covered her mouth in disbelief. 'And it says... whoever holds this note becomes the new creditor!'"

1892587113.m_KeyValue: ""'...Finally, the villagers must throw you off a 99-meter cliff into the sea and back... 99 times... for a thorough baptism by the ocean.'""

1892587116.m_KeyValue: ""'I told you...' Lamia reacted instantly, using a servant as a springboard to leap up. Before the ball could fall completely, she raised both hands—""

1892587117.m_KeyValue: ""Tris intercepted the speeding fish-skin ball with perfect precision—or rather, it was as if the ball itself had eagerly rushed to meet her fist.""

1892587118.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh my, what are we going to do about this? It's quite a pickle.' Somehow, Acappella had already freed herself from Empousa's binding vines through unknown means.""

1892587119.m_KeyValue: ""And now, the fish is dead, its skin made into a ball for sport. So... following the phenomenon described, shouldn't the net be destined to break? Doesn't that make sense?""

1892587120.m_KeyValue: ""Stopping a short distance behind Empousa, Lamia gathered herself before throwing the fish-skin ball high into the sky—""

1892587121.m_KeyValue: "'Since when are Bell Ringers above the rules!'"

1892587122.m_KeyValue: ""'Hmph, so much for being some fancy ex-commander of whatever.' Though Empousa spoke dismissively, her stance remained alert. 'Now watch this—Harvest Season!'""

1892587123.m_KeyValue: ""'Tch...' At that same moment, Lamia recognized the predicament. She immediately withdrew her foot, spinning gracefully in the air to disperse her momentum before landing elegantly.""

1892841792.m_KeyValue: "Clear [Sapphire Isle] <color=#a65f30>N 1-5</color>: Becoming Lord of the Isle"

1893615121.m_KeyValue: "Randomly spawns 4 Lava Crystals on the Battlefield which resonate after a certain period to deal high M. DMG to enemies."

1898863124.m_KeyValue: ""'What an incredible ability! Come on, tell us what you've seen!'""

1898863125.m_KeyValue: ""Moments later, Aiona returned to the fireplace, her expression serene. 'The true owner of this place,' she said, her voice as calm as a still pond, 'is not Leonardo Ptolemy.'""

1898863126.m_KeyValue: ""Aiona approached the manuscripts once more, invoking her ability. The text fragments swirled and danced, breaking apart and reforming, as they transported her consciousness back through time.""

1898863128.m_KeyValue: ""Gilrain pondered for a moment, then asked, 'So, did Nikola steal Leonardo's identity to gain greater fame?'""

1898863129.m_KeyValue: ""'I couldn't see how Nikola's story ended, but Leonardo Ptolemy has most likely passed away. He was a remarkable painter.'""

1898863130.m_KeyValue: ""'Hold on, wasn't he supposed to be dead?'""

1898863131.m_KeyValue: "'The one who built this place was Nikola.'"

1898863134.m_KeyValue: ""'I agree with Friedrich. In the story I saw, they made a promise to explore the world together.'""

1898863135.m_KeyValue: "'I don't think he needed to use Leonardo's name to succeed. These maps are exceptionally well-made.' Friedrich leaned in to examine the map his companion was holding."

""'Pay the price, and they'll be yours.'
Hallon believed the words in that mysterious letter. He could no longer save the Isle or its people. All he could trade for was the safety of a precious few.
The rest—infected or not—would be nothing more than drops in the ocean. That was the Bell Ringer's flawless form of purification.
'One last request... If you find my nephew, Isaac... If there's any hope left for him...'
Albrecht neither nodded nor shook his head. Hallon couldn't read his expression.
It had taken all his courage to make a deal with the Bell Ringer—under the guise of establishing liquid metal currency. He fled with Constantine in tow.
Run! Get Bella from the basement and leave now!
He didn't know that what awaited him… was his daughter's lifeless body.""

1914218439.m_KeyValue:
""The broken Siren's Tear lay on the table, its luster dulled by the passage of time. From deep within, it stirred a whisper of song.

A young girl stood at the weathered bow of a ship, softly humming to the moon.

By the time she was born, the Pillars of Hercules had long since vanished beneath the waves. Her people had become wanderers, adrift on the sea. Her mother had told her, that they were like fish, and the currents chose their path.

She had not yet learned to turn her tentacles into legs, nor to speak the language of humans. But her song carried a quiet yearning—what lay beyond the waters, on those distant, unknown shores?""

1914240564.m_KeyValue: "A spectral entity capable of marking and assaulting enemies from afar. It's advised to steer clear of its attack range."

1914988922.m_KeyValue: "'That's far from mere superstition! There's a documented case of someone's wish being granted by a shooting star.'"

1914988923.m_KeyValue: ""'What a load of nonsense!' Empousa scoffed, her disdain for such starry-eyed notions palpable.""

1914988924.m_KeyValue: "'But didn't he also claim that he didn't believe stars could foretell the future?'"

1914988925.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh, but it was a disaster. The marriage alliance between the Berde and Yegar Kingdoms became a threat to the kingdom in the west.'""

1914988927.m_KeyValue: ""'I've made my choice. I must revive my family. I have my own mission, so I'm staying here,' Jestel declared, finally at peace with her decision.""
