2689733929.m_KeyValue: "This is the first time I've heard you speak so softly. Are you really..."

2689734061.m_KeyValue: ""They're armor inhabited by lost souls, remnants of Baphomet's experiments. Leave them to me!""

2689734096.m_KeyValue: "Baphomet... 'the Soulless'? As in the Elder? He did all this?!"

2689734259.m_KeyValue: "This bat... it's... here to help us?! Aren't they supposed to be on the same side?"

2690191806.m_KeyValue: "We shall release them from their torment."

2690200533.m_KeyValue: "Is this my reward for completing my task?"

2691302612.m_KeyValue: "Artifact Patrol are special units that patrol through the ship's cabin. Memorize their routes to avoid being spotted."

2692038461.m_KeyValue: ""In my opinion, we should keep the menu as it is. Let the younger generation taste the hardships we endured in our day!""

2692038527.m_KeyValue: ""This policy is essential to preserving our family's power. If everyone is granted the freedom to take the long sleep, what will happen when war breaks out and they all choose death out of fear? Such a dangerous precedent must not be set under any circumstances.""

2692038558.m_KeyValue: ""Now is absolutely not the time to be training spies. In my opinion, we'd best hold off on this for now.""

2692038624.m_KeyValue: ""Though the Bathory family is regaining its glory, we remain frail compared to the Kingdom and the Church. Only by prioritizing the family's benefit can we ensure our people thrive.""

2692038659.m_KeyValue: ""In my view, the evening gatherings must not be abolished. These young ones, they merely wish to laze about in their coffins.""

2692038690.m_KeyValue: "An untamed animal running wild in the castle could not only damage our antique furniture but also frighten our vassals. We absolutely cannot allow this! It's out of the question!"

2692038756.m_KeyValue: ""However, after all this time, most of the pages must have yellowed and wrinkled... Procuring new books isn't cheap. In my opinion, we should save our resources for now.""

2692038791.m_KeyValue: ""During the Holy War, we didn't even have houses. Who cared about curtains when we were sleeping in cellars? In my opinion, this expense is unnecessary.""

2692038888.m_KeyValue: ""What we need right now are practical skills and survival strategies. Instead of practicing singing, they should focus on perfecting techniques to precisely sever the major arteries of the Church's soldiers. Let's just forget about this.""

2693159781.m_KeyValue: "Losing Vassals will slow down the Bloodsoul Recovery."

2698757730.m_KeyValue: ""'Interestingly, this key, unearthed alongside the linen, bears a similar eye-shaped emblem. I can't help but wonder what they might lead to.'""

2698757731.m_KeyValue: ""A lake crowned the hill, its shape and color like an azure iris. It transformed the hill into a colossal eye fixed upon the heavens, its gaze eternal and unwavering.""

2698757733.m_KeyValue: ""'Looks like you've cracked it too,' Friedrich said, picking up one of the manuscripts and placing it next to the one in Gilrain's hand.""

2698757734.m_KeyValue: ""If you could see Gilrain's expression right now, it would undoubtedly be a sight to behold.""

2698760994.m_KeyValue: ""The way it was said—so casual, so unconcerned—you'd think the cat was talking about something else entirely.""

2698760995.m_KeyValue: ""—Wait. Upon closer inspection, that was just Theophane, calmly walking ahead to lift the flap.""

2698760996.m_KeyValue: ""'...Meow? Staring at me won't help, meow... Zzz...'""

2698760997.m_KeyValue: ""A breeze rustled the travel tent, lifting the flap just enough to reveal a black kitten curled in a nest, eyes half-lidded in a lazy doze. 'Mmh... they're here, meow.'""

2698760998.m_KeyValue: ""'Ah, yes. This morning's reading said I'd encounter a woman with the initial J, atop a mountain with a lake, sometime this afternoon…'""

2698760999.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh, I know. Lovers is a pair, so it ought to be doubled. But even then, it only reaches twelve. Still less than thirteen. Which makes this my victory.'""

2698761000.m_KeyValue: ""...Sure, there might be no rules, but you can't just do whatever you want! Where's the dignity of the Church in all this, Vice-Commander!?""

2698761001.m_KeyValue: ""With a flick of its left paw, three Tarot cards flew cleanly from the top of the deck, landing face-down on the table before the two people—and itself. 'Why, by whose reading turns out more accurate, of course, meow.'""

2698761005.m_KeyValue: ""'But why was it given to us?' Theophane hesitated. 'I mean, we didn't exactly win that match...'""

2698828514.m_KeyValue: """"Ah... you're right.' Agares stopped and turned to face Noah. 'Tell me. Why do you think that is?'""

2698828515.m_KeyValue: ""'Fair point...' Agares paused, as if something had just occurred to him and turned to face Noah. 'How about this? You'll be my next Vice-Commander. What do you say?'""

2698828516.m_KeyValue: "'The stench is too strong for something that's been sitting underground for ages.'"

2698828517.m_KeyValue: ""('So he's found something... That means he won't ask me to help, right?')""

2698828518.m_KeyValue: "W-What? Has the real one already been revealed just like that?!"

2698828519.m_KeyValue: ""'I'm in a sour mood right now, dear imposter.' Twin Agares raised a hand and flames sparked to life in his palm, radiating blistering heat.""

2698828520.m_KeyValue: "Noah remained noncommittal. 'Even so... why did you take Agares's form?'"

2698828521.m_KeyValue: "'The real Agares has never done that.' Noah took several steps forward. 'Unless... neither of you is the real one.'"

2698828523.m_KeyValue: "'...they fuse into a burning sun—like the man who constantly sets himself ablaze.' Mass gave a bitter smile and shook her head. 'But it's all just an illusion.'"

2698829602.m_KeyValue: ""Suddenly, Darcias pinned Acappella against a gravestone. As she drew closer, it became impossible to tell whether the encroaching cold came from the graveyard or Darcias.""

2698829604.m_KeyValue: ""'Seems broken. Won't open.' After a few whimpers, the stone door stopped shaking.""

2698829605.m_KeyValue: ""The air grew colder in the space between their frozen gazes. Had the silence shown emotion, it surely would have exclaimed, 'This is a graveyard!'""

2698829606.m_KeyValue: ""*cough* As a tale by the greatest bard of Minexus, it’s flawless, of course. I definitely did not get carried away and added a few lines on the spot. *cough cough*""

2698829607.m_KeyValue: ""'And this is a heated showdown between two lead singers!' Acappella placed her hands on her hips, her eyes blazing with determination.""

2698901474.m_KeyValue: "Hati could vividly picture the scene: the Garlic knight not only had to fend off their father but also block any attack that might harm the animals or even a tree."

2698901475.m_KeyValue: ""'However, I believe that in warriors' contests, utilizing the environment is crucial. So in that match with your father, if we had seen it through to the end, he probably would have won.'""

2698901478.m_KeyValue: ""Clive, however, pressed on, his battle cries echoing with each wild swing of his short sword. The fire of youth had clearly ignited his temper.""

2698901479.m_KeyValue: ""'Looks like I need to hit the road, or I'll start rusting away,' Gadric said, catching Hati by surprise.""

2698901480.m_KeyValue: ""'But... but...' Clive stammered, his convictions visibly shaken.""

2698901481.m_KeyValue: "Gadric settled himself on the stone steps and began to savor his lunch."

2698904741.m_KeyValue: ""'There is,' Empousa unexpectedly provided the answer. 'They ensured that this Fangtooth Tower stands tall and unshaken to this very day!'""

2698904742.m_KeyValue: ""'Later, the attackers tried setting fires at the base of the tower, but even this failed to drive out the stalwart Ganelon defenders.'""

2698904743.m_KeyValue: ""'What do you mean it's not?' Empousa put her hands on her hips. 'We Bathorys successfully repelled the enemy, thanks to the intel we got from Fangtooth Tower!'""

2698904744.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey Hati, I've heard the sunset here is beautiful. Is it true?' Empousa asked.""

2698904745.m_KeyValue: ""'All the land on the Howling Peninsula was forcibly occupied by your family,' Empousa shouted, hands on her hips. 'I've told you to read more, you dim-witted wolf!'""

2698933058.m_KeyValue: ""'The Bathory family's loyalty was once unquestionable. When the goddess commanded them to cede a portion of their lands to their despised rivals, the Ganelon family, they obeyed, surrendering territory to those contemptible mongrels.'""

2698933059.m_KeyValue: "'We seek texts or treatises concerning the art of alchemy.'"

2698933060.m_KeyValue: ""Under the moonlight, they came upon an even more out-of-place metal instrument. Even the moonlight twisted and coiled around it, as if being inexorably drawn into its otherworldly form.""

2698933061.m_KeyValue: ""'Let's go,' Piera decided. 'No point wasting time here. We'll go in and see for ourselves.'""

2698933065.m_KeyValue: ""Cain's mockery left the three deeply unsettled—each silently praying it wasn't true, for if it were, their faith would crumble to dust the moment they stepped out of the church.""

2698934018.m_KeyValue: ""And someone who spends all day chasing after fun has no right to judge them, do they?""

2698934019.m_KeyValue: ""'Acappella. If I'm not mistaken, weren't you supposed to be out gathering herbs with Darcias today?'""

2698934020.m_KeyValue: "—Why did both of them fall for it!?"

2698934021.m_KeyValue: "'And this sword-and-shield symbol likely represents the Gravekeeper.'"

2698934023.m_KeyValue: ""What? Skip? What does that even mean—skip what!? You think dropping a cryptic, cool-sounding line gets you off the hook!? Explain the rules, Bell Ringer!""

2698934024.m_KeyValue: "Note: A 'Slap' may be a bit exaggerated."

2698934025.m_KeyValue: ""'He's sacrificing six cards at once… Such a massive cost—could it be…' Thibault's voice was lower than usual, as if she already foresaw the coming storm of molten fury.""

2698934026.m_KeyValue: ""'Blegh… ptooey!' Acappella grimaced in utter disgust, glaring at Darcias with venom in her eyes. 'Dar—cias! What was that for—'""

2698973348.m_KeyValue: ""'That contract was to fulfill a promise. At a friend's grave, he swore a solemn vow—to erect a haven for travelers against nature's fury.'""

2698973349.m_KeyValue: ""'An intriguing tale, indeed. I perceive the message you aim to convey.'""

2698973350.m_KeyValue: ""'Is this pitiful grass huddling together for warmth, or a deception woven by oleanders blooming in a parched riverbed?'""

2698973351.m_KeyValue: ""'In fact, they did something that everyone considered foolish, even cowardly—they built a simple waystation right where they were, merely 3 miles from Iron City.'""

2698973352.m_KeyValue: ""'Be careful not to startle the little one in your hands,' Yggdrasill said, his words reflecting the boundless patience he had for his pupil.""

2698973353.m_KeyValue: ""'Would you permit me to share his story with you?' Edina asked, sitting upright in her chair, hands folded neatly on her lap.""

2699004930.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey, that's cheating!' Hati cried out, dashing after her. To her surprise, Ami had already beaten her to it.""

2699004931.m_KeyValue: ""The windmill's creaking seemed to intensify, its cacophony growing so fierce it raised doubts about its structural integrity. It was as if the old mill was desperately pleading for one last chance to serve before being destroyed by the merciless march of time.""

2699004934.m_KeyValue: ""'They clearly had no concept of financial planning,' Empousa scoffed, her voice dripping with disdain and unwarranted superiority.""

2699004935.m_KeyValue: ""'Stop showing off knowledge you've picked up from books,' Hati called out Empousa. 'Cleaning a mill requires a lot of water and is usually done after the harvest season. It's not something that happens frequently.'""

2699004936.m_KeyValue: "'Yes. Legend has it that the Bathory family head who spearheaded the effort to aid Ganelon vehemently cursed the Ganelon family before he was killed.'"

2699004937.m_KeyValue: ""Empousa exclaimed eagerly, 'And wasn't that a perfect opportunity to bring the Ganelon family over to the Bloodborn side?'""

2699010244.m_KeyValue: ""Empousa sighed. 'Don't tell me you didn't like them back then, so you tossed them on the roof, and now you're regretting it and coming to find them?'""

2699010245.m_KeyValue: ""Hati sat on the roof, clutching the gloves and gazing up at the full moon as it emerged from the dispersing dark clouds.""

2699010246.m_KeyValue: "Hati interjected: 'I recall reading in the family records that a Bathory ancestor was killed after being struck by lightning. Perhaps that explains Empousa's fear.'"

2699010247.m_KeyValue: ""'Say, Empousa, I was thinking... Could it be that you're afraid of lightning because it can suddenly light up the sky like the sun?'""

2699010248.m_KeyValue: ""Now the mill's windmill no longer spun idly. Its interlocking gears drove the millstone, steadily grinding out sack after sack of easily storable flour.""

2699010249.m_KeyValue: ""On the mill's final night of operation, Hati used a wrench to disengage the gears connecting the windmill to the mechanism below. However, she deliberately left the switch that locked the windmill's rotation in place.""

2699076802.m_KeyValue: ""—But seeing the complex expressions of hard-fought victory on everyone's faces, Noah paused, thought for a moment, and decided to keep those words to himself.""

2699076804.m_KeyValue: ""'On second thought, explaining would be too much work.' Before even starting, Agares quickly abandoned the idea and turned toward the hot spring.""

2699076805.m_KeyValue: "—And there was his characteristic sigh of resignation."

2699076807.m_KeyValue: ""'Now now, let's not go around calling people sources of contamination,' Agares said with a resigned shake of his head. 'And if we're talking about the Plague, wouldn't that be you?'""

2699076808.m_KeyValue: ""'Ow ow ow...' Hati winced as she struggled to climb out of the pool. 'The mist here is so dense—even our hometown, Mouret, can't compare...'""

2699076809.m_KeyValue: ""'I told you not to force yourself to come along,' Noah said, gently patting Hati's back. 'We've only just set sail, so there's still time to turn back if you want.'""

2699077762.m_KeyValue: "...Never mind! Your opinions don't matter! Let’s refocus our gaze on the scene at hand!"

2699077763.m_KeyValue: ""No, no, no... That can't be true! Because...""

2699077764.m_KeyValue: "'Gadric won’t escape this time. I’m more curious how far he'll go.'"

2699077765.m_KeyValue: "'—isn't a full-moon night!' Nicole's pupils contracted. 'Which means… he never said that line tonight!'"

2699077766.m_KeyValue: ""'Acappella vanished early this morning. Probably off chasing her next thrill.' She raised an arm and examined it briefly, as if checking her own vitals.""

2699077767.m_KeyValue: ""'Gadric...' Nicole flicked droplets from her hair, '...once told Edina that he wore the helmet because, like plants, he didn't need to eat.'""

2699077768.m_KeyValue: ""(All right, we've driven him into the deep end. Now we wait.)""

2699077769.m_KeyValue: ""Nicole smiled and raised a single finger. Droplets slowly beaded at the tip. 'With this, of course.'""

2699077774.m_KeyValue: ""'Weeding's no fun at all. How did that garlic-head even put up with this?' The so-called Gadric grumbled a few complaints, then raised a hand in a familiar gesture...""

2699148682.m_KeyValue: ""After an eternity of anticipation, the last grain of sand finally trickled through. The (ostensibly) 'solid gold' (but secretly hollow) Statue of Goldland triumphantly flipped over and stood erect, its arms outstretched as if to embrace the heavens!""

2699148683.m_KeyValue: ""Interestingly, judging by its weight, that sculpture was clearly hollow and merely gold-plated... The reasoning behind this peculiar design? Well... that's another sad story altogether.""

2699148684.m_KeyValue: ""'Exactly! Goldland amassed enormous profits through seafood smuggling, throwing the entire Minexus seafood market into chaos. Every family on the continent has reached their breaking point with him.'""

2699148685.m_KeyValue: ""'Hah, I know what you're thinking: that I alone can't defeat both of you.' Van Helsing said, all the while scanning his two opponents, watching for any sudden moves to pursue Goldland.""

2699148686.m_KeyValue: ""In a flash, Van Helsing grasped the truth: The real Seafood Tycoon Pearl had never been in that dilapidated shack—it had been here in the square all along! The recent explosion had caused it to transfer directly into Noah's body!""

2699148687.m_KeyValue: ""Before Noah could finish speaking, a nimble figure suddenly sprang out from the side, lunging fiercely at Cain!""

2699148689.m_KeyValue: ""'Well, I never saw this coming. I was on the brink of making a grave error. As always, Silver-haired one, your insight puts me to shame.'""

2699150853.m_KeyValue: ""'Em-Empousa?!' After quickly checking Empousa was unharmed, Lamia turned to face Tris. 'You bastard! Looking to start a war with the Bathory? I don't care if you're from some choir—'""

2699150858.m_KeyValue: ""'A contest...?' Lamia crossed her arms, eyeing Tris suspiciously. 'You're not planning to use this as a cover for something else, are you?'""

2699150859.m_KeyValue: "Her words brought an immediate silence—she had clearly struck a chord; everyone present obviously had more important matters to attend to."

2699150860.m_KeyValue: ""'Should be around here somewhere, Commander.' Acappella casually flipped open a nearby wooden box. 'Though... I wonder what you plan to do with 'that thing' once we find it?'""

2699150861.m_KeyValue: ""'If you keep dragging your feet, I'm leaving without you, you dummy Empousa!'""

2699150863.m_KeyValue: "'Not if I can help it!' Acappella pointed at Lamia with a finger-gun gesture. 'Just so we're clear—I won't go easy on you like the Commander does.'"

2699150864.m_KeyValue: "'Wh-what's the big deal? That doesn't seem so difficult!'"

2699153994.m_KeyValue: ""Agares slicked his hair back with a sweep of his hand, then paused, eyes glinting with some fresh mischief.""

2699153996.m_KeyValue: ""…Wait, when did he get so philosophical?""

2699153997.m_KeyValue: ""Still reeling from the sheer audacity, Noah finally spoke. 'You're the one who pushed me in.'""

2699154000.m_KeyValue: ""The finish line drew near… but suddenly, chaos erupted in the water—""

2699154001.m_KeyValue: "Noah slipped out from under his arm without a word."

2699156166.m_KeyValue: "'Could this be what Cain meant by something that could enhance our family's power...!'"

2699156167.m_KeyValue: ""Acappella stood there stunned, her mouth opening and closing as words failed her.""

2699156170.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey, hey...' Acappella made a token attempt to twist free, then protested halfheartedly when she realized she couldn't move. 'Isn't this against the rules?'""

2699156171.m_KeyValue: ""Before Empousa could finish her words, the fish-skin ball crashed into the fishing net with thunderous force, creating a massive depression in the net that seemed ready to tear it apart.""

2699156172.m_KeyValue: ""'Acappella, a Bell Ringer shouldn't say such things.' Tris walked toward the torn net. 'The Bathory ladies have won this match—after all, I did break the rules.'""

2699156173.m_KeyValue: "Empousa unconsciously clenched her fists at her sides. 'Something that could enhance our family's power... Could it really be hidden in such an unremarkable fishing village?'"

2699156174.m_KeyValue: ""'Come forth, my servants—Scarlet Vassal Dance!' Before Lamia could finish speaking, four Scarlet Bats appeared, swirling around her.""

2699156175.m_KeyValue: ""'While the rules don't explicitly forbid using our abilities, still...' Tris pondered with her chin in hand, completely unfazed by the fish-skin ball that Acappella had just sent skyward.""

2699156176.m_KeyValue: ""'Go forth, my servants!' Four Scarlet Bats heeded the command and intercepted the ball's trajectory, their wings beating in unison to create a whirlwind that might slow its advance.""

2699156177.m_KeyValue: ""'Ugh! You're so annoying!' Empousa exploded, hands on her hips as she stomped her foot. 'Standing there gloating with that fake sweetness...'""

2699889061.m_KeyValue: "Survive the siege of the Nightmares for 60 sec."

2708624968.m_KeyValue: "Double Speed has been activated. We can now adjust the flow of time in battles."

2708624969.m_KeyValue: ""For example, right now the flow of time is twice its normal speed.""

2708624970.m_KeyValue: ""In the future, you can adjust it here as needed.""

2708625128.m_KeyValue: ""Remember, each Vassal has their own Moon Phase.""

2708625129.m_KeyValue: ""From left to right, they are Full Moon, Crescent Moon and New Moon.""

2708625130.m_KeyValue: "I have marked the three Moon Phases for you."

2708625131.m_KeyValue: ""When I'm deployed, the skill indicator will show the target I'm about to aim at.""

2708625132.m_KeyValue: "I will target an enemy and fire at it the moment the battle starts!"

2708625141.m_KeyValue: ""Once the moon meter is full, Blood Moon can be summoned and bring enormous aid to the fight.""

2708625142.m_KeyValue: ""Whenever there are Vassals of 3 different Moon Phases present, the battle may become more favorable.""

2708625161.m_KeyValue: "It will allow you to flexibly utilize our formation and skills to adapt to any situation!"

2708625163.m_KeyValue: "Leave it to me. Handling solitary enemies is my specialty!"

2708625164.m_KeyValue: "Observe the battlefield and enemy formations during combat."

2708625166.m_KeyValue: ""That enemy may be isolated, but seems like it could be tricky to deal with.""

2708680415.m_KeyValue: ""Every {0} sec, deals DMG equal to {1} of Max HP, stacking up to {2} times.""

2709254980.m_KeyValue:
""When the battle begins, the ally on this tile is granted Lunar Halo.
Lunar Halo: Once HP falls below 60%, Lunar Halo will restore {0} of Aiona's Max HP to the bearer, then disappear.""

2709255046.m_KeyValue: ""When the battle begins, Ami Soul Links with the Vassal on the tile. Soul Link applies All DMG Taken Down (Minor) to both Ami and the unit. The effect is permanent and cannot be dispelled.""

2711121847.m_KeyValue: "Major Arcana Card No. 11. Dalcarlo's Divination: _$$Justice radiates where universal principle and holy faith convene._$$"

2711793352.m_KeyValue: ""Legend has it that this Celestial God bore the responsibility of nurturing and caring for the celestial realm. They secluded themself in a corner of the celestial realm, sacrificing the freedom to roam, instead mating with powerful Celestial Gods to give birth to offspring, tirelessly working for the realm's prosperity and longevity. Those inspired by this Celestial God will gain the ability to communicate with all things.""

2713788949.m_KeyValue: ""Throws a coconut shell at a select location, dealing weak P. DMG to all enemies in a circle and inflicting Stun for {0} sec.""

2713788982.m_KeyValue: ""Throws a feast at a select location, causing all allies to move there. Upon arrival, they gain ATK SPD UP by <style=""Highlight"">{0}</style> for {1} sec.""

2713789048.m_KeyValue: "Clive's Sword. Summons wolves to deal moderate P. DMG to enemies in range."

2715425773.m_KeyValue:
""Averdin had never known this basement existed beneath his brother's residence.
Labeled vials lined the shelves. Inside jars, dark gray tissue floated. As Averdin stepped closer, he saw slender fingers webbed with translucent skin.
'Averdin, why are you here...'
'What have you done?! We promised to give the sirens a home—and you did all this behind my back?'
An argument erupted at once, escalating from plea to fury to despair, until someone knocked over the reagent shelf. Glass vials shattered like wine glasses from Bella's celebration.
A shard sliced across Averdin's hand. It burned.""

2716297271.m_KeyValue: ""Sealed within a Salt Coffin, it gains a Shield equal to {0} HP and recovers {1} HP per sec. Once the Shield is destroyed or HP is fully restored, it gains the ability to move.""

2716585384.m_KeyValue: ""It might be unthinkable to mortals, but we are called the Bloodborn precisely because we possess the coveted secret to immortality...""

2716585385.m_KeyValue: ""*Sigh* Even though these Pure Blood Essences are from my personal stash... Here, take them.""

2716585386.m_KeyValue: ""Lady Empousa is in great danger. Time is of the essence, so let's talk on the road.""

2721557976.m_KeyValue: ""'Maybe... we should make a wish too, if we see another shooting star,' Noah suggested hesitantly.""

2721557978.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh, that reminds me! I recently read about that shooting star from 400 years ago in a book: The Red-Haired King found it and used it to forge the Magic Blade!'""

2721557979.m_KeyValue: ""'Well, at least the prince and princess were buried together in the same tomb, united for eternity.' Perhaps Aiona's comforting skills could use a bit of refinement.""

2726187950.m_KeyValue: ""'Cain, I have to say, your words are truly revolting.'""

2726187953.m_KeyValue: ""'See, Cain?' The painting on the wall suddenly spoke. 'Even these children have noticed your abnormal behavior.'""

2728883392.m_KeyValue: "Cannot be targeted by enemies (can take AoE DMG)."

2730750356.m_KeyValue: "Memory: As Tears Fade Into The Sunset"

2732373697.m_KeyValue: ""It fits light equipment, offering outstanding attack.""

2737852473.m_KeyValue: ""Oh no... what do I do now?! Her silence is terrifying! Silver-haired friend, say something!""

2737852474.m_KeyValue: ""That's right! If we collect them all, we can awaken the complete Bella! And redeem her life from Joyce!""

2737852475.m_KeyValue: "And if I choose to continue living as I am?"

2738506034.m_KeyValue: ""Since the dark-skinned lady here seems intrigued, please follow me.""

2741215275.m_KeyValue: ""When the battle begins, gains Dodge Rate UP (Minor) for {0} sec.""

DMG to enemies in a rectangular, inflicting Bleed, lasting {1} sec. DMG increases with each time. The second hit Knockbacks enemies, and the third causing significant Knockback.""

2743400228.m_KeyValue: "'Come on! Eye of God belongs to the Bathory family—I'd know it anywhere.'"

2743400229.m_KeyValue: ""And yet, I found myself drawn instead to the shifting path of the moon, to the hidden patterns among the stars.""

2743400231.m_KeyValue: ""The stars shifted, time passed, and still, Aiona's research showed little progress.""

2743400232.m_KeyValue: ""'Even within the Alita family, it's rare to see an astronomer of such natural brilliance.'""

2743400234.m_KeyValue: "'I wonder where the last of the pages could be…'"

2743400235.m_KeyValue: "They found the remaining pages without incident."

2743401316.m_KeyValue: "'Though this one doesn't look like another lunar phase record.' Noah carefully took the final page in hand."

2743401317.m_KeyValue: "'Got something! This looks like the last record—let me take a look…'"

2743401318.m_KeyValue: ""Amid the quiet of the observatory, the sounds of a 'treasure hunt' echoed in every corner.""

2743401319.m_KeyValue: ""'If you can be here, why can't we?!'""

2743573380.m_KeyValue: ""Note: At the Puppet Association's request, we include their promotional list for discounted items. The list reads: 'Our store's motto is: If a wealthy customer and a Bell Ringer fall into the river at the same time—'""

2743573381.m_KeyValue: ""Gilrain stared at Baphomet with a half-smile. Those eyes seemed to pierce through the ancient armor, probing the secrets hidden within.""

2743573382.m_KeyValue: ""The cruel words hung in the air, as if freezing the very atmosphere... This verbal assault landed with nothing short of a fatal blow!""

2743573383.m_KeyValue: ""A deep, hoarse sound emanated from Baphomet's armor as it shifted: 'To think that I, in my twilight years, should find myself reduced to such a state. I, who was once feared throughout the realm as the 'Soulless'—""

2743573387.m_KeyValue: ""'Of all the creatures in the world, why did it have to be a cat? Don't they realize just how many people are allergic to cats?'""

2743574340.m_KeyValue: ""Baphomet adopts the bearing of a seasoned Grand Elder, imparting wisdom to his juniors with paternal gravitas.""

2743574341.m_KeyValue: ""Until it spotted a rusted trophy and trotted over. Like a lion toying with its prey, the cat curiously batted at the trophy with its paws.""

2743574342.m_KeyValue: ""The other three elders snapped their attention to Baphomet—now the most venerable and influential figure within the family. He gazed across the gathering, then slowly began to speak—""

2743574343.m_KeyValue: ""'Sigh, as the newest elder, I guess I will handle this intrusion,' Gilrain shrugged resignedly as he conjured a scythe and dragged it out of the room.""

2743612580.m_KeyValue: ""'Something... is calling to me...' Out of nowhere, a glimmer appeared, fluttering around Bella in lazy spirals before landing atop the wick of a candle embedded in the stone wall.""

2743612581.m_KeyValue: ""'Ah... well, that's just how silver-haired is!' Selena nodded knowingly. 'Lord Van Helsing said silver-haired love sneaking around in the dead of night, doing who-knows-what.'""

2743612582.m_KeyValue: ""With a gentle smile, she took Selena's hand. Her radiant expression seemed to soften even the unforgiving blaze of the midsummer sun.""

2743612583.m_KeyValue: ""'T-t-too close!' Selena's face flushed bright red—like a thoroughly roasted octopus. In that dazed instant, her thoughts drifted back to several months ago...""

2743612584.m_KeyValue: "'Why can't you give up that ridiculous octopus?'"

2743612585.m_KeyValue: ""'Hmph. Already trying to wriggle out of your duties...' Selena glared at Bella, clearly displeased.""

2743612586.m_KeyValue: "'Lost? That's nothing to worry about!' Selena showed no hint of distress at the news. 'We'll journey across the whole of Minexus... and uncover ingredients of legend!'"

2743612587.m_KeyValue: ""A firefly appeared from nowhere, spiraled gently around the girl, then disappeared into the streets. Selena never noticed.""

2743612592.m_KeyValue: ""She took Bella's hand. 'So... will you help me make this dream come true, Prep Cook Bella?'""

2743612593.m_KeyValue: ""Bella looked up at her call, following the direction of Selena's outstretched finger—though she still kept Selena pinned beneath her. 'Is that... parchment?'""

2743613670.m_KeyValue: ""'Hmph,' the portrait spoke again. 'I must concede, you meddlesome creatures have achieved some competent attempts at understanding matters beyond your comprehension.'""

2743613672.m_KeyValue: ""'That's right,' Cain affirmed. 'It's merely an art piece created through alchemy.'""

2743613673.m_KeyValue: ""'I don't understand a word you're saying, Cain!' Lamia bursted out.""

2743613674.m_KeyValue: ""'Of course I remember,' came a reply from the painting. Cain, it seemed, hadn't been talking to himself after all. The portrait—none other than that of Limine Bathory, the Matriarch herself—had spoken.""

2743613675.m_KeyValue: ""As for what Lamia did that angered the elders—that's another tale for another time. After all, every story has its bounds.""

2743645253.m_KeyValue: ""Thus, a grand Bloodline Transfusion scheme, entangling all existing families, was about to be realized. However, fate intervened when Noah and his allies struck down the plan's mastermind, narrowly escaping catastrophe.""

2743645256.m_KeyValue: ""Baphomet was sinking into despair, realizing that this meeting was likely to end on Bella's relentless prattle.""

2743645257.m_KeyValue: ""Just then, with a meow, the black cat—predictably the last elder to arrive—leapt onto its seat and promptly dozed off.""

2743645258.m_KeyValue: "'You're just bitter because Friedrich beat you for the Bell Ringer position!' Bella ruthlessly exposed Gilrain's true motives. 'That's why you're trying so hard to belittle the Roland family!'"

2743645259.m_KeyValue: "'There's a girl from the Ganelon family who's rumored to possess considerable power.'"

2743717128.m_KeyValue: ""The three of them gazed into the Ancestral Vault, shrouded in black mist, each harboring the same guess about the girl's identity.""

2743717129.m_KeyValue: ""'Hmph, you expect me to believe that?' Isaac scoffed, his face etched with disdain.""

2743717130.m_KeyValue: ""'I actually know a bit about it,' Noah said. 'I've done extensive research in the archives before coming here.'""

2743717131.m_KeyValue: ""In truth, the protagonist’s presence was far from coincidental. The longer he resided in the castle, the more the mysterious chamber captivated his curiosity. Thus, the three agreed to explore it together.""

2743718084.m_KeyValue: ""To Empousa's right, naturally, was their esteemed guest. 'Honestly, I don't really mind. Bella, what do you think?' Lorelei shrugged nonchalantly, then turned her head to the right.""

2743718085.m_KeyValue: ""Before Bella could finish her sentence, the candle in her hand gave a soft hiss and fizzled out.""

2743718087.m_KeyValue: ""It earned its nickname from the way it hunts—by launching jets of corrosive fluid, like fiery darts of liquid glass. With its firm flesh and notoriously difficult capture conditions, the Raog Fin Shark is hailed as the crème de la crème of Minexus’s Eight Great Delicacies.""

2743718088.m_KeyValue: ""The hazy moonlight cast a faint glow across Bella's face, tinged with something almost like regret. She pressed her lips together, hesitating, before speaking softly. '…I haven't paid off my last deal with her.'""

2743718089.m_KeyValue: "'…I trust I don’t need to spell out what needs to be done.'"

2743718091.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh? Did something happen to Bathory Castle?' The guest, unsurprisingly, was far more composed than her hosts.""

2743718096.m_KeyValue: ""Well, except for Ami. She simply looked like she was itching to digest—no, defeat—the sea monster.""

2743718097.m_KeyValue: ""'You did walk off with thirty bolts of my silk, twenty crates of tea, and a priceless navigational chart!'""

2744937277.m_KeyValue: ""Here, you can undertake daily training. These challenges will not only enhance your Blood Power but also grant rich rewards.""

2745867911.m_KeyValue: "Is this my reward for completing my task?"

2745867912.m_KeyValue: ""As a token of gratitude, I will mend your wounds next time.""

2745867913.m_KeyValue: "What a gentle audience you are... Then I shall accept your gift."

2745867915.m_KeyValue: ""What a hassle... Picking out a gift in return is no easy task, you know?""

2745867920.m_KeyValue: ""Is this a bounty? Strange, I haven't taken any jobs recently.""

2746761411.m_KeyValue: ""Only the enemy in the spotlight can use Ultimate, but takes 50% more DMG.""

2746993870.m_KeyValue: ""_$$The Star_$$ can fire an arrow in a select direction, eliminating the first enemy in its path and lighting any torch mechanisms it passes. The fire arrow has no effect on Artifact Captains.""

2747454174.m_KeyValue: ""Eldest of the Bathory family, and guardian of the Bloodborn. Despite his proud demeanor, he isn't immune to the ravages of time.""

2751557963.m_KeyValue: ""Summons a Spectral Wolf, dealing moderate P. DMG to enemies in range.""

2754020956.m_KeyValue: "Ah... the _$$Threads of Fate_$$ always bring unexpected clarity."

2754094916.m_KeyValue: ""Jestel, I leave the flank to you!""

2754095048.m_KeyValue: ""I can't believe I was praised by the great Aiona, the one close to the renowned Moonblessed...""

2754095083.m_KeyValue: "What... What am I supposed to do?"

2754095114.m_KeyValue: ""Now is not the time to play the hero, Miss Bloodborn.""

2758698911.m_KeyValue: ""Well done, Noah. I've prepared everything you'll need from now on. Follow me.""

2758709009.m_KeyValue: ""It's so dark in here, not a speck of light... Would it be too late to change our minds?""

2758709011.m_KeyValue: "These phantoms are memories which have slipped here from other realms. It seems today we're dealing with a realm ruled by Blood Servants."

2758709012.m_KeyValue: ""That's what everyone says. Well, let me first provide you with some guidance.""

2758709014.m_KeyValue: ""Now, time for you to deal with them. And don't fear the unknown—you're stronger than you might imagine.""

2758710034.m_KeyValue: "The 'Pure Blood Essence' within is exactly what newly turned vassals desperately need."

2758710035.m_KeyValue: "Pure Blood Essence? Does that mean... they have to drink blood?"

2758710036.m_KeyValue: ""Pure Blood Essence is precious sustenance for the Bloodborn. I understand this transition is difficult to accept right away, but it's necessary to gain power.""

2758710037.m_KeyValue: ""Eating when hungry, wanting to live when sick—setting aside our conflicts, can humans and Bloodborn be similar creatures? I understand now. To 'live,' we drink.""

2760793166.m_KeyValue: ""'What? How would that work?' Bella asked, tilting her head in confusion. 'Wouldn't the bloodlines be completely incompatible?'""

2760793167.m_KeyValue: ""In truth, the Bathory family was once an ordinary family on the continent, until one of them caught Dracula's eye and was transformed into a Bloodborn.""

2760793169.m_KeyValue: "'There is another option: we could attempt a Bloodline Transfusion using the bloodline of other families.'"

2761039794.m_KeyValue: ""Sometimes, we don't need to find a way out—we just need to keep moving forward.""

2761039795.m_KeyValue: "Of course... I should have known. We're all caged beasts—how could we possibly hide weapons outside the castle?"

2761039796.m_KeyValue: "No. 66 always said the wind outside the castle sounded different from within."

2761420321.m_KeyValue: ""For each Element, I foresee that you may encounter 1 to 3 Trials.""

2771387969.m_KeyValue:
""Beneath the waterfall, I heard a clamor.
It seemed like two voices engaged in an argument,
Or perhaps the lament of a solitary soul.
I heard a voice speak of life's torment,
_$$Death is what keeps us from ever smiling again._$$
Another voice arose, softly praising life's treasure,
_$$Legacy is what allows us to bask in light._$$
I moved forward,
But there was no one in sight—only a white flower entwined with thriving grass.
The petals were withered,
Yet the grass was lush.""

2771518348.m_KeyValue: ""But when two hearts beat as one, even chaos can become a sweet melody.""

2771518349.m_KeyValue: ""So, you should start thinking about what game we'll play next.""

2771518350.m_KeyValue: ""Tell me, why is your heart racing so wildly right now?""

2771518352.m_KeyValue: "Stop pretending! You should be awake by now!"

2771518355.m_KeyValue: ""Yes, I was overthinking things. I apologize.""

2771518356.m_KeyValue: "But I have no idea what kind of _$$commotion_$$ to cause yet."

2773792560.m_KeyValue: ""And now, to protect that happiness… I have even more reason to recover my sorrow.""

2773792562.m_KeyValue: ""After that, Tris brought me to the Church. I underwent the Silver Blood baptism.""

2779625023.m_KeyValue: ""But now, as our family stirs once more, it is time to awaken them, to let them bear witness to our rebirth and rising glory.""

2808063013.m_KeyValue: ""A winged creature from the depths of the sealed area, corrupted by Black Blood. It appears to have been driven from the darkness by some force. Covered in dry blood spots, it generates powerful Sound Waves with each flap of its wings.""

2808063014.m_KeyValue: ""Master Vendor, thank you for creating us! But why call us Sirens? Must we endure this torment for our home?""

2808063015.m_KeyValue: ""Master Vendor, thank you for creating us! But why call us Sirens? Must we endure this torment for our home?""

2820055662.m_KeyValue: "Thank you for bringing a moment of joy to this long and wearisome life."

2838920207.m_KeyValue: ""'It seems the recent disturbances in the Ancestral Vault were likely caused by this traitorous Ancestral,' Noah deduced.""

2846647951.m_KeyValue: ""A boater hat forgotten by time and space. This eerie relic bore witness to the rightful deaths bestowed by Ottavia, the _$$judge._$$ In another life, would her devotion to her beliefs have tempered the hatred she held for her sister?""

In another life, after conquering the Calamity, would she have endured the excruciating pain caused by the Black Blood within?""

2846647955.m_KeyValue: ""Branches forgotten by time and space. Seemingly ordinary, yet it was part of Yggdrasill, the _$$world tree._$$ In another life, would he have remained detached from the world, or longed for power over it?""

2846647957.m_KeyValue: ""A great axe forgotten by time and space. Its stunning color was meticulously crafted by a blacksmith for Baphomet, the _$$new noble._$$ In another life, would this newly fashioned noble have discovered another way to protect his family's legacy?""

2846647958.m_KeyValue: ""A jellyfish forgotten by time and space. These red and black aquatic creatures were the cherished pets of Ami, the _$$head of Landis._$$ In another life, as she led her family through the Calamity, would she have realized she unleashed a power that could be a curse?""

2846821165.m_KeyValue: ""Twin guns forgotten by time and space, adorned with beast-heads, the proudest creation by the _$$charming rascal_$$ Van Helsing. In another life, as he reveled in joy and madness, would he finally encounter a worthy adversary?""

2846821167.m_KeyValue: ""A crown forgotten by time and space. Black was the color for Joan, the _$$rebel._$$ In another life, after toppling the old order, might she have chosen peace to claim her victory?""

2846821168.m_KeyValue: ""A boater hat forgotten by time and space. This eerie relic bore witness to the rightful deaths bestowed by Ottavia, the _$$judge._$$ In another life, would her devotion to her beliefs have tempered the hatred she held for her sister?""

2846821170.m_KeyValue: ""A butterfly knife forgotten by time and space. Carrying the aura of sin, it belonged to Hati, the _$$vigil of plague,_$$ who sealed the Calamity within herself. In another life, after conquering the Calamity, would she have endured the excruciating pain caused by the Black Blood within?""

2846821172.m_KeyValue: ""Branches forgotten by time and space. Seemingly ordinary, yet it was part of Yggdrasill, the _$$world tree._$$ In another life, would he have remained detached from the world, or longed for power over it?""

2846821173.m_KeyValue: ""A jellyfish forgotten by time and space. These red and black aquatic creatures were the cherished pets of Ami, the _$$head of Landis._$$ In another life, as she led her family through the Calamity, would she have realized she unleashed a power that could be a curse?""

2846821174.m_KeyValue: ""A great axe forgotten by time and space. Its stunning color was meticulously crafted by a blacksmith for Baphomet, the _$$new noble._$$ In another life, would this newly fashioned noble have discovered another way to protect his family's legacy?""

2849365771.m_KeyValue: "But you never thought to say goodbye to her."

2849365772.m_KeyValue: ""_$$I wanted to protect everyone, but in the end, I was the one being protected all along._$$""

2849365773.m_KeyValue: ""_$$The hopes Father entrusted to me, the future Clive Jr. passed on, and the power you've given me... I no longer need your protection._$$""

2849365774.m_KeyValue: ""You've grown so used to those chains that, even though removing them would set you free, they've become a part of who you are.""

2849842916.m_KeyValue: ""Control: Strong. The carrier cannot be targeted. Unable to cast Ultimate, Specials, Basic ATK, or move during the effect.""

2849842917.m_KeyValue: ""Control: Strong. The carrier stops and remains unable to cast Ultimate, Specials, Basic ATKs, or move during the effect.""

2850875127.m_KeyValue: ""As a representative of the Bathory family, you must have heard of the Carrelles? Once one of the twelve noble clans, like your own. They were tasked with guarding the Heart of the Divine Body.""

2850875129.m_KeyValue: ""Looking back, I never questioned it at the time. I thought it meant we were a family. Until the eldest son of the Carrelle family came and chose the strongest among us...""

2850875130.m_KeyValue: ""Judging by your tone, he wasn't simply picking out slaves for labor in the city, was he?""

2850875131.m_KeyValue: ""How ironic. We thought we were slaves who, despite our hardships, still owned our lives...""

2850875132.m_KeyValue: ""But in Lord Carrelle's eyes, we weren't even human. Our true purpose had always been to become the firewood that keeps the Heart beating.""

2850875133.m_KeyValue: "The Heart must keep beating. And each pulse requires a living soul burned to ash to keep it going."

2850875134.m_KeyValue: "So that's why he chose the strongest..."

2850875137.m_KeyValue: "The people living in that manor now... Are they the descendants of your former companions?"

2850875138.m_KeyValue: "Should I say you have a kind and naive side too? That place was rebuilt to house war orphans like myself."

2853655638.m_KeyValue: ""Pardon my indifference, but an observer should not intervene too much.""

2853658839.m_KeyValue: "Perhaps we should weigh our options more carefully."

2858644133.m_KeyValue: ""Deals <style=""Highlight"">30%</style> increased DMG to targets inflicted with Burn.""

2860689945.m_KeyValue: "The key is within reach. Let's take a break."

2860691991.m_KeyValue: ""Thanks for all the assistance, by the way... I'm still getting the hang of it all.""

2860692022.m_KeyValue: ""Here, we can learn about a Vassal's past, as well as present. We can also explore the unique memories you've created together.""

2860693080.m_KeyValue: ""Hmph, well at least someone is doing something for once.""

2861254505.m_KeyValue: "Repel the Church's elite forces sweeping through the village."

2861626541.m_KeyValue: ""Units that pass through the werewolf's Blood Trail will be inflicted with Pestilence, taking DMG equal to a percentage of their Max HP per sec, while boosting DMG dealt by {0}. This effect lasts until the end of the battle.""

2866015054.m_KeyValue: ""The moon is but a dream of the sun, and thus we were forgotten by the light. Born of darkness, yet imprisoned by it. To Empousa, a Bloodborn's immortality is not a gift but a curse—daylight exists as an unreachable shore. The Bloodborn took her freedom, while her position as the Bathory family heir stripped away her identity. She seeks a key—one that would free her from this cage called 'Empousa'...""

2879689000.m_KeyValue:
""Clear Tomb of the Fallen - Restless Spirit II Fragment 2 to randomly obtain equipment from the following. 
<alpha=#80>Time erodes the husks of monsters, but the legacy of battle echoes eternally.""

2882379912.m_KeyValue: "You may access Tomb of the Fallen through the Lost Courtyard."

2883671346.m_KeyValue: "The time has come to restore this curious _$$game._$$"

2883671377.m_KeyValue: ""Servants of the demon, you will know true despair!""

2883671536.m_KeyValue: "Let's take the leader down and win this for Jestel and the victims!"

2888616689.m_KeyValue: "Slaves of House Carrelle who will stop at nothing to claim a _$$surname_$$ for themselves."

2891614809.m_KeyValue: "Perform Spirit Siphon with any Vassal {0} time(s)."

2892644678.m_KeyValue: ""Amusing... since when does tattered armor need sleep? Save your barbs, traitor. I will teach you a hard lesson myself!""

2892720464.m_KeyValue: "Piera's Bond. Greatly increases CRIT Rate and CRIT DMG for all allies right away."

2894967240.m_KeyValue: ""When enemy units burrow, they gain {0} DMG Reduction. However, they will surface as Control effects inflicted on them continue. Each instance of Control extends the duration of these effects on the enemy by {1}.""

2897354208.m_KeyValue: "A summon that performs Basic ATK on enemies ahead in a cone. Only 1 can exist at the same time."

2899212100.m_KeyValue: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 6"

2899212103.m_KeyValue: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 3"

2899212104.m_KeyValue: "Unlocks after activating Talent Tree - New Recipe 5"

2901751951.m_KeyValue: ""Learning it was Noah's idea, Jestel sighed resignedly, 'I've told you before, Noah. It's impossible to keep a castle this huge clean.'""

2901751954.m_KeyValue: "'I thought this place could use a bit of tidying up.' Noah finally unveiled his decidedly mundane motivation."

2902264080.m_KeyValue: ""To my accomplice, and to the coming war.""

2902264082.m_KeyValue: "It's no different from what the Carrelle family did back then."

2902264083.m_KeyValue: ""With these azure flames that grant second life, you raised an army to stand against the Church, commanding the dead to fight for you.""

2909075243.m_KeyValue: "You win this time. I can't stand it!"

2915247733.m_KeyValue: "Received P. DMG and M. DMG reduced by {0}."

2919273108.m_KeyValue:
"Bella: Alright.
Yakov: As expected of Noah!"

2919275286.m_KeyValue: "What do I think? No objections from me."

2919276309.m_KeyValue: ""This approach seems fine, but I'll review it or any potential oversights.""

2919418183.m_KeyValue: "Though come to think of it—are you sure you're up for staying out late?"

2921341097.m_KeyValue: ""Heir to the Bathory family, his behavior is whimsical and irascible, exuding not a hint of the expected aristocratic bearing.""

2921341099.m_KeyValue: "Butler and personal alchemist of the Bathory family. Obsessed with creating the perfect Bloodborn specimen."

2921341100.m_KeyValue: ""Heir to the Cidhall Family, who finds a confidant and competitor in Friedrich.""

2921341102.m_KeyValue: ""One of the surviving Bloodborn Elders, rumored to have bought her elder position with a hefty sum. She runs the Puppet Association spanning across the continent.""

2922785798.m_KeyValue: "Different Vassals wear different equipment types. You can use the Quick Equip feature to quickly swap a Vassal's gear."

2926521177.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Headgear</style> A headpiece worn by Piera that emanates a lambent glow.
Silk ribbons embroider the restless mind of the Bone Collector. Pray tell me, are white lies truly kind, or are they deception?""

2926521179.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Ring</style> Piera's cherished ring, seemingly symbolizing a pact made with someone.
Could internalizing one's pain be a form of deceit?""

2926521180.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Outfit</style> The shawl worn by Piera, stitched ornately.
Carefully, she collects the sorrows of the dead, folding each piece meticulously then stacking them on her shoulder, waiting for the pain to absorb into her.""

2926521182.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Amulet</style> Piera's collection of skulls, her constant companions.
Pristine white bones, each a testament to the girl's acts of redemption. She convinces herself this is a form of kindness.""

2926521210.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Headgear</style> The blazing crown of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Bearing the sparks of hope, he brought them to the mortal realm, only to be judged by the gods as a thief.""

2926521211.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Outfit</style> The black robe of Agares the Beguiler, which suppresses his high-temperature scales. It is imbued with the primal power of War.
As the Flaming Chariot raced across the sky, he removed one of his own ribs, using it as kindling to cast the first ray of light.""

2926521212.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Ring</style> A ring forged from the blood of Agares the Beguiler, imbued with the primal power of War.
Iron nails pierced the chest, and hot blood stained the mountainside. Gazing down at the smoke billowing in mortal realms, he finally found solace as he closed his eyes.""

2926521213.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Amulet</style> Agares the Beguiler, after being consumed by flames, left only a few feathers as proof of his existence in this world.
As he opens his eyes once more, wings grew from his spine, and his hunger drove him to gorge on entrails. Alas, he was never a hero, but a vulture who drank the blood of heroic memories.""

2926521570.m_KeyValue: ""<style=""EquipposHL"">Amulet</style> The Wolfsbane plant means something special to the Clive family.The ballad goes: _$$Wolfsbane blooms beneath the moon's soft grace; The promised home waits beyond the sky's embrace._$$""

2926521573.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Headgear</style> A hood that Clive would always wear before he turned into a beast.
_$$Children say I look scary, but admire me in battle. So I keep this thing on for them, I suppose. Until the grave calls me._$$""

2926521575.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Ring</style> The iron ring worn by Clive.
Alas, the abyss looms nigh. Proceed, and let darkness consume thee; Retreat, and let fear erode thy soul.""

2926521576.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Outfit</style> The robe that Clive often wore.
The moonlight shone coolly, and the air filled with frost; The long night approached, yet the will to light was never lost.""

2926521601.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Amulet</style> Jewelry that never left Goldland's possession.
_$$Listen. This is all I have to leave you with. Adorn it, and seek your own freedom._$$""

2926521606.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Headgear</style> Goldland's stylish cravat, clean and exquisite.
It still retains a faint scent, one that seemingly blends beauty and maturity.""

2926521607.m_KeyValue:
""<style=""EquipposHL"">Outfit</style> Goldland's silk white shirt, completely spotless.
Though his elegance and grandeur may not be genuine, the effort placed into preserving purity is appreciable.""

2926521608.m_KeyValue:

It represents the lofty status of the Landis family. From material to craftsmanship, it perfectly complements its current owner, and yet not once has he worn it.""

Welcome to the Minexus continent. Please accept our tokens of camaraderie. We wish you an exhilarating journey ahead.""

2935877478.m_KeyValue: ""A lowly cleric in the Tempus Church who uses incense to ward off Black Blood. When their <color=#D63536>chant is complete</color>, they heal nearby allies. Interrupt when possible.""

2935877480.m_KeyValue: "A melee creature mutated by Black Blood. Focus fire to eliminate quickly."

2935877483.m_KeyValue: ""If left alone, these tentacles will deal high AoE DMG. Prioritize eliminating them.""

2935877484.m_KeyValue: ""A ranged creature mutated by Black Blood. When their <color=#D63536>chanting</color> is complete, they deal high DMG and inflict Stun. Interrupt when possible.""

2935877487.m_KeyValue: ""The crab's body has been fully crystallized by salt. Land CRIT Hits to shatter the crystal, but be cautious of its corrosive acid that hits in a straight line.""

2935877488.m_KeyValue: "The crab's body has been fully crystallized by salt. Land CRIT Hits to shatter the crystal and reduce its DEF."

2935877511.m_KeyValue: ""War Machines shoot arrows that penetrate targets, dealing Continuous DMG.""

2938692410.m_KeyValue: ""A pity I've cast aside my humanity... but for you, I suppose I'll make an exception.""

2938692441.m_KeyValue: ""Ah, this feeling... it's as if I've been transported back to the past. Thank you for allowing me to experience life once more.""

2938692476.m_KeyValue: ""I am a servant of God, why do my hands tremble...?""

2938692507.m_KeyValue: ""How did you know I… Wait, I should prepare something too…""

2938692573.m_KeyValue: "Your insistence leaves me no choice but to accept."

2938757919.m_KeyValue: "I never thought I'd be fighting shoulder to shoulder with a Bloodborn."

2938757920.m_KeyValue: "Shoulder to shoulder? We're standing miles apart."

2938757922.m_KeyValue: "Is this the true power of blood?"

2941544064.m_KeyValue: ""To take the name ""Thibault"" is to mask the past beneath a facade. Though Ressa once swore to sacrifice everything, what choice must she make when Noah stands between her and the path to progress and redemption?""

2941544073.m_KeyValue: ""A mysterious fortune teller who emerged on the El Dorado. Shrouded in enigma and intrigue, she refers to others by the faces of Tarot cards.""

2941544075.m_KeyValue: ""As the Third Mate of the El Dorado, William holds a position of leadership, yet remains somewhat estranged from the rest of the crew. Meanwhile, his relationship with Captain Goldland is also... rather unusual.""

2941544076.m_KeyValue: ""Past regrets become lessons for today. This time, things will be different...""

2941544077.m_KeyValue: "Sunset Isle resident and long-time friend of Noah and Ressa. Formerly a subject in the Church's Ascension Experiments."

2949225602.m_KeyValue: ""An outgrowth of an infected rough-skinned newt. Now autonomous, this creature retains the will of its former self, spraying toxins upon death in attempt to take its enemies down with it.""

2949225603.m_KeyValue: ""The Blood Beast encountered on the El Dorado is a rare amphibious creature. The toxins it releases, amplified by Black Blood corruption, are particularly terrifying.""

2949225613.m_KeyValue: ""A common tusked wild boar on Sunset Isle. With a fiery temper and poor eyesight, it charges indiscriminately when provoked.""

2988881070.m_KeyValue:
""Humans are food.
That was the first thing my sister told me when I arrived in the territory. Her voice was unfeeling, as I stood at the edge of the bustling crowd.
They looked like me. Moved like me. I couldn't understand how she saw them as nothing more than prey.
But then a girl approached. She carried flowers and a scent—not of petals, but something irresistible.
It struck a chord somewhere primal. My doubts trembled.
'Can you feel it? This is food.'
Then my sister placed the little girl's hand into mine, her crimson eyes shimmering with ravenous hunger.
Perhaps it was an invitation—to blood. She handed me a dagger, the Bathory crest gleaming on it. 'She is yours now.'
And just like that, she vanished, leaving me alone with the girl. The girl held out a flower. 'Lord asked me to give you these.'
'Why?'
'It's for your birthday... You must really love flowers, miss?'
Do I? I don't know.
But at that moment, the fragrance of blossoms masked the thirst in my chest...""

2988883248.m_KeyValue:
""PH-Mouret, a town in the northwest of The Howling Peninsula, is part of the Ganelon family. Recent cases of suspected Black Blood disease have emerged, and all former Gravekeepers have vanished after leaving their posts, prompting a secret investigation. 
Investigation revealed that local water has been contaminated. The source is the <style=""Highlight"">'Child of the Plague', Sheila the Firstborn, who was watched by the Ganelon family for generations.</style>
The cause of the previous Gravekeeper disappearances remains unclear. The current Gravekeeper, Clive, shows signs of beast transformation and is suspected to working with the Child of the Plague to accelerate the spread of the Black Blood disease. 
The Black Blood disease is a divine punishment from Aeon. Carriers gradually lose their sanity and become uncontrollably violent. <style=""Highlight"">If left unchecked, no pure land will remain in Minexus. Thus, Thibault, Bell Ringer No. ⅩⅠ, has ordered the purge of Mouret. May Aeon's gospel heal this land tainted by the Black Blood.</style>
—Tempus Church Investigation Manuscript Ⅰ 

An undocumented outbreak has occurred in a northern village affiliated with Bathory. 
Investigation revealed that <style=""Highlight"">Hati the Secondborn, also known as 'Plague's Origin,' </style> passed through the area and caused an illness through scales. She has been added to the pursuit list. 
—Tempus Church Investigation Manuscript Ⅱ""

3029779175.m_KeyValue: ""A junior sorcerer of the Church, entrusted with reciting the powerful spells from the hallowed scriptures. <color=#D63536>Capable of executing a lethal blow to clustered heretics</color>.""

3041025830.m_KeyValue: ""To help us on the journey ahead, we need to use Blood Enhancement.""

3041034014.m_KeyValue: ""As far as I know, the Bathory Castle is woven with a hidden network of underground passages. In keeping with the First Tenet of Secrecy, the ancient lords carved out a vast subterranean city—once the secret base of the family's operations.""
