3054617287.m_KeyValue: ""We all know how bad-tempered Elder Bella's little puppets can be... If we impose price controls, they might just pack up and leave. What'll we do then?""

3054617384.m_KeyValue: "Sounds like an impartial and highly professional organization. I say we let them survey our territory! They might help us learn more about our family history. I'm all for it!"

3054617551.m_KeyValue: ""Not only is this place surrounded by mountains on three sides, but there's also a river on the east side flowing towards The Howling Peninsula. Anyone traveling by water must pass through here. It's a perfect haven.""

3054617617.m_KeyValue: ""Let me speak up for the person in question! The one sending letters is an old acquaintance from before they joined the Bloodborn. Although an outsider, they bear no ill will towards the Bloodborn.""

3054617648.m_KeyValue: ""To restore our family’s glory and conquer the continent, our Vassals must venture forth and gain worldly knowledge. We need only ensure they exercise discretion in their affairs.""

3054617683.m_KeyValue: ""Word on the street is that this Bloodborn faction differs greatly from the Bathory—they live among humans, with similar eating habits and lifestyles.""

3054617714.m_KeyValue: ""Absolutely support it! From major decisions like the power to execute vassals and the right to use high-level Alchemy, to minor ones like daily menu planning and choosing the castle's furniture style... the elders want to control everything!""

3054617749.m_KeyValue: ""Raising taxes can only solve our immediate needs. In the long run, it's not a good solution and will inevitably cause discontent among vassals and believers. It's time we explore new ways to earn Soli and acquire resources!""

3054617780.m_KeyValue: "These Ganelon people have lost their families and leaders. They're in a precarious situation where they could be purged by the Church at any moment. Now is precisely when they need protection."

3054617846.m_KeyValue: ""Indeed, this is a good opportunity. Although they've made it clear they have no intention of getting involved in the conflict between the Bloodborn and the Church, they're quite generous in other aspects.""

3054988091.m_KeyValue: ""'Cease this pointless deliberation. My eyes shall light the way. Mind your steps and follow me closely.' With these imperious words, the Roland heir strode away, his customary arrogance trailing in his wake.""

3054988092.m_KeyValue: ""'Would you rather it be called one-eyed hill?' Friedrich jested while attempting to bump shoulders with his stern companion. But Gilrain, in anticipation, nimbly stepped out of the way.""

3054988093.m_KeyValue: ""To Friedrich, however, his companion's tone seemed more resigned than angry.""

3054988094.m_KeyValue: ""'How interesting. When pieced together, they reveal a hidden message.'""

3054988095.m_KeyValue: ""'So this cabin was built by the cartographer, Leonardo Ptolemy? Probably to study this Eye of God.'""

3054991354.m_KeyValue: ""'Where's the shopkeeper?' Joan glanced around the dim tent interior, but saw no sign of anyone else. Her brows drew together—clearly unimpressed by a fortune-telling tent run by a single cat.""

3054991356.m_KeyValue: ""But seriously, why did it have to end every sentence with meow? Where had it learned that annoying habit!?""

3054991358.m_KeyValue: ""'I knew Bell Ringers don't play by the rules…' The cat froze mid-groom, clearly taken aback. 'But this is the first time I've ever seen it in action, meow...'""

3054991359.m_KeyValue: ""'Theophane, stand down.' Joan raised a hand to stop him. 'I believe I said this was my war. You don't need to force your hand.'""

3054991360.m_KeyValue: ""Joan hesitated for only a moment before lifting her chin, a confident smile playing at her lips. 'Interesting. No matter the kind of war, I don't lose. I accept your challenge.'""

3054991361.m_KeyValue: ""'...then I might be willing to share a little information.' Having said its piece, the cat paid no further heed to the Bell Ringer and her Vice-Commander. Instead, it resumed licking its paw, as though entirely disinterested in doing business.""

3054991364.m_KeyValue: ""Joan turned the crystal ball over in her hand. 'Because it reeks of Silver Blood. For the Bloodborn, it's the most potent poison.'""

3054991365.m_KeyValue: ""…Wait, hold on. Divination is that precise? That’s not divination, that’s a prophecy!""

3055058874.m_KeyValue: ""'Touché. Come now, we've got to unwind every now and then...' Agares waved his hand with a laugh. 'Or... we might end up as one of the Ascendants.'""

3055058876.m_KeyValue: "('Wait... we have to fill it back in? Ugh. Guess I'll need to find an excuse.')"

3055058877.m_KeyValue: "Surely Agares and Goldland couldn't be more different... right?"

3055058878.m_KeyValue: ""The tiny flame left Twin Agares's palm and caught the wind. In an instant, it swelled into a roaring blaze—ready to engulf Agares whole.""

3055058879.m_KeyValue: ""'Then... this meteorite-looking thing you're holding, what is it?' For the third time, Noah edged another step back.""

3055058880.m_KeyValue: ""Both _$$Agares_$$ froze, startled expressions spreading across their faces. Now that they've been exposed, what will they do?""

3055058881.m_KeyValue: ""He... he's got a point. Given Agares's personality, it really is hard to imagine him initiating something like that. One point to Agares!""

3055058882.m_KeyValue: "Noah gave a slight nod. 'So you're the same. The past you cling to still runs through your blood.'"

3055058883.m_KeyValue: ""Mass knelt slowly, running her fingers once more across the weathered surface of the gravestone. '...he hasn't been back in a long time. Maybe he never will. So I came in his place.'""

3055059962.m_KeyValue: ""After all, Bell Ringer No. X has absolute control over the 'Air'—this is her domain.""

3055059966.m_KeyValue: ""Well, the Church's machine has become this remarkable—even capable of expressing sorrow.""

3055059969.m_KeyValue: "'Objective eliminated.' A flash of light was all that remained. Darcias had already struck down the enemy before the blade could even be glimpsed."

3055059972.m_KeyValue: ""'Since when?' A fire seemed to burn in Acappella's eyes. 'Of course it's when the static arises again, that's... the new chapter of life!'""

3055059973.m_KeyValue:
""'KHHK SHHK HHKH SHHK
KHKH SHHK HHKH SHHK'
It started writhing—oh, I mean dancing.""

3055114574.m_KeyValue: ""Secret passages will instantly transport you, like a portal.""

3055131834.m_KeyValue: ""'Curious about the outcome of my last duel with your father?' Gadric asked suddenly, a slight smirk playing on his lips.""

3055131835.m_KeyValue: ""'Suddenly, someone rushed in to stop us,' Gadric said, pouring himself another glass of wine.""

3055131836.m_KeyValue: "'No. She returned east five years ago and reportedly fell in battle.'"

3055131839.m_KeyValue: "But Clive was deaf to any counsel. His mind was fixated on one goal: to land even just a hit."

3055131840.m_KeyValue: ""'Uncle Gadric, did you really just fall by accident?' Clive finally asked the question that had been on both siblings' minds.""

3055131841.m_KeyValue: ""'There are many types of warriors in this world—those who fight on land, at sea, and from afar. This title of the kingdom's First Knight is nothing but empty words.'""

3055135101.m_KeyValue: ""'In response, the Bathory family launched a massive assault on the tower. This time, their forces included numerous Bloodborn, who could transform into bats and fly directly up the tower.'""

3055135102.m_KeyValue: ""'In the stories passed down through generations in the Aegis family, the Church was merely using the Ganelon family as pawns to trap the Bathory family on The Howling Peninsula.'""

3055135103.m_KeyValue: ""'In fact, the tower is mentioned countless times in the castle's archives and various historical records. It has been destroyed at least thirteen times throughout its history.'""

3055135104.m_KeyValue: ""'How many years can your puny memory even span, you dumb wolf!' Empousa exclaimed, exasperated by the futility of reasoning with her.""

3055163418.m_KeyValue: "'Those belong to the Church!' Isaac exclaimed vehemently."

3055163419.m_KeyValue: ""The black-haired man turned to face them. 'Curiosity is the crucible of growth for the youth, but it can also bring a premature end.'""

3055163420.m_KeyValue: ""Fortunately, their master had provided them with an old map of the church from its time. Although the building was now unrecognizable, the map at least helped them locate the library's position.""

3055163424.m_KeyValue: ""'Yet, as he prayed, his son had already aged to become as old as him.'""

3055163425.m_KeyValue: ""'Perhaps the reward was bestowed in ways beyond their perception,' Nicole advocated for the goddess.""

3055164379.m_KeyValue: ""'At least this time it's not _$$my back hurts_$$ again. But the mission's already over—no more excuses to slack off, right?'""

3055164380.m_KeyValue: "'Let's do something fun!' She looked expectantly at the other two Bell Ringers—"

3055164381.m_KeyValue: ""'Right, right… That's the one. Hmm… I've seen it in a divination shop before… What was it called again…?' Agares stepped forward, equally invested in the invisible mystery.""

3055164382.m_KeyValue: ""'In any case, there are twelve cards for each of the four suits—forty-eight total. Then there are the rest: cards with no suit and no number. Altogether, that brings the full deck to ninety-six.'""

3055164383.m_KeyValue: ""…Wait, what!? That has nothing to do with paths or stones!""

3055164384.m_KeyValue: ""'By skipping the action phase, Agares loses one-eighth of his maximum life, but avoids triggering Silvershade Requiem's counterattack—a cautious yet calculated choice.'""

3055164386.m_KeyValue: ""Up until now, the battle had been a chaotic free-for-all—But in this moment, Acappella and Thibault exchanged a glance, and without a word, a silent alliance was formed.""

3055164387.m_KeyValue: ""Having also recovered after eating the mushroom, Agares wore a drained expression. 'Ugh… What were we even doing just now…? This is bad. My stomach's killing me. I need a hot spring…'""

3055203706.m_KeyValue: ""'This butterfly, with its broken wings, may well be oblivious to the terror of death.'""

3055203708.m_KeyValue: "'But they did not fulfill their original task.'"

3055203709.m_KeyValue: ""'Master, I truly believe that goodness prevails in this world. Just as the foreman emerged from the tent, ready to face his end alone, some of the workers who had departed earlier returned.'""

3055203710.m_KeyValue: ""Legend tells that long ago, these snowy plains were even colder than they are now. Travelers heading north often froze to death before reaching Iron City. No ordinary person could endure such bitter cold.""

3055203711.m_KeyValue: ""Finally, Edina, after being interrupted several times, couldn't help but blurt out in a childish tone, 'Master, do you even want to hear this story anymore?'""

3055203713.m_KeyValue: "'Why do you insist on saving it?' The Master's eyes remained utterly devoid of emotion."

3055235290.m_KeyValue: ""'That decision lies with the Elders. At present, they are inclined to avoid conflict with the Church, so it's unlikely they will expand into Mouret for the time being. However, I cannot speak for future intentions.'""

3055235291.m_KeyValue: ""'No,' Hati said with a bitter smile. 'He cursed the Ganelon family, saying that one day they would be unable to harvest from their own estate.'""

3055235294.m_KeyValue: ""Hati glanced up at the idle gears above, powered by the windmill. 'Of course we can eat it. The bread is mostly dark, but it's quite tasty. After all, this is the only mill in all of Mouret town.'""

3055235296.m_KeyValue: ""'To ensure the Ganelon family wouldn't face starvation in the following winter, the Bathory family even joined in the farming efforts.'""

3055235297.m_KeyValue: ""'But then, someone arrived with sacks of flour and taught the Ganelon family how to bake black bread.'""

3055240604.m_KeyValue: ""'Or maybe you were traumatized by a past event that you have blocked from your memories,' Ressa added.""

3055240605.m_KeyValue: ""Empousa clenched her fists and shouted, 'Then why in the world did you throw them onto the mill roof?!'""

3055240606.m_KeyValue: ""As Ressa and Empousa prepared to ascend to the roof, they were met with an unpleasant surprise: the ladder was broken.""

3055240607.m_KeyValue: ""'It happened during one of the castle's expansions,' Empousa's now calm voice replied. 'That particular individual was consumed by an insatiable obsession to reach the moon, which manifested in relentlessly expanding the castle up toward the sky.'""

3055240609.m_KeyValue: ""'Sounds like a minor thing from the way you're talking,' Ressa replied.""

3055307162.m_KeyValue: "*Sigh* '... Guess we're down to our last option.'"

3055307163.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey! You can’t hog the hot spring all to yourself!' Hati shouted, dashing over. 'Let’s settle this with a race to the hot spring!'""

3055307164.m_KeyValue: ""'As you might have guessed, it’s just a dormant volcano...'""

3055307165.m_KeyValue: "'Hold on—this type of coin... A special minting technique is used to make the heads side heavier than the tails! That's not fair!'"

3055307166.m_KeyValue: "'There's no need to complicate things—there're still—'"

3055307167.m_KeyValue: ""'My, my. I specifically planted a sapling by this spring three years ago to keep it private, yet here you all are...'""

3055307168.m_KeyValue: ""Soon after, they disembarked at Ethereal Springs, embarking on their journey to discover the fabled hot spring.""

3055308122.m_KeyValue: "'Oh... mercury poisoning?' Darcias took just one-eighth of a breath to piece it all together."

3055308124.m_KeyValue: ""'It was on a full-moon night...' A familiar voice echoed from the distance, but the thick mist made it impossible to see who was speaking.""

3055308125.m_KeyValue: ""Moments later, the swirling mist began to dissipate. Before Darcias and Nicole stood a patch of empty ground. And Gadric's voice... was gone.""

3055308127.m_KeyValue: ""Of course, this mission was entirely self-assigned, which, in a way, meant she had already become a rather capable Vice-Commander. As for why she went to such lengths...""

3055308128.m_KeyValue: ""'Ahahahahaha!' The laughter grew louder, as if he'd just heard the funniest joke in the world.""

3055308129.m_KeyValue: "It looked like the two of them were clearly up to something. Things were starting to get interesting..."

3055308134.m_KeyValue: ""'But once he gets serious, he's surprisingly troublesome.' With a wry smile, she shook her head. 'Come on. We're not getting anything else tonight.'""

3055308135.m_KeyValue: ""Wait, what? He can form a Covenant? That's a power reserved for Bell Ringers and only the most elite combatants.""

3055379042.m_KeyValue: ""'—the one and only Kristoph Goldland!' Admiring the masterpiece in his palm, Goldland declared with unbridled enthusiasm, 'For us merchants, time is not merely precious—it is the very essence of gold itself!'""

3055379044.m_KeyValue: ""A ray of sunlight broke through the clouds and mist, enveloping Van Helsing in a golden glow. In this moment, he stood as the veritable incarnation of wisdom and strategy.""

3055379045.m_KeyValue: ""'Begins now!' The words had barely left his mouth before Goldland took off like a shot, his boisterous laughter echoing behind him. 'Ha ha ha ha! Van Helsing, stop them!'""

3055379046.m_KeyValue: ""The thin mist was dispersed by the gust of wind from the figure's movement, revealing none other than Goldland himself. 'Cain, I never expected you to uncover Lord Goldland's secret.'""

3055379047.m_KeyValue: "Noah felt a chill down his spine. He and Ami had once profited from selling overpriced seafood to Friedrich... Could this be the real reason the Church was targeting him?"

3055379048.m_KeyValue: ""'Ah... It's all coming back to me now. Those grueling days, huddled together on that rickety little boat... How could I have strayed so far from my original purpose?'""

3055379049.m_KeyValue: ""This realization flashed through Van Helsing's mind like lightning. In the very next heartbeat, he sprang into action, lunging forward and wrapping his arms around Noah's waist, forcefully yanking him backward!""

3055381212.m_KeyValue: ""Tris clapped her hands and said with a smile, 'Now, now, it's just a friendly match. Let's not spoil the mood. After all, we might not see each other again after this, right?'""

3055381213.m_KeyValue: ""'Well, of course it's...' Empousa suddenly realized something. 'Ah!'""

3055381218.m_KeyValue: ""'Tris, former commander of the Church choir.' Tris gave a slight nod. 'So, young ladies of Bathory, I assume you're also here for 'that thing'?'""

3055381219.m_KeyValue: ""'Going by their aura, they must be from the Bathory family.' The golden-haired woman turned to Acappella. 'Acappella, you sensed it too, didn't you?'""

3055381220.m_KeyValue: "'Ugh... why do we have to go to some backwater fishing village...' Empousa muttered under her breath. 'And with Lamia of all people—'"

3055381222.m_KeyValue: "'Then... let's say you can only touch the ball three times after it reaches your court.' Tris held up three fingers. 'Touch it a fourth time and you lose the point.'"

3055381223.m_KeyValue: "'Ah...!' Empousa finally realized. 'Then the force keeping the sand from falling in is...'"

3055381224.m_KeyValue: "Tris set up the fishing net vertically. 'This net will serve as the boundary between our two teams.'"

3055381225.m_KeyValue: "'Appreciate it?' Empousa's brow furrowed. 'The Bathory family needs no charity from the Church!'"

3055384354.m_KeyValue: ""Noah hesitated, then sighed. 'I just wanted to watch the sea, not take a dip in it.'""

3055384355.m_KeyValue: ""Noah gave him a long, bewildered stare, as if unsure whether he heard Agares correctly.""

3055384357.m_KeyValue: ""'The sea isn't all allure. It's not just the pale blue you see from here—the depths are black like tar, thick enough to drown out the loudest screams.'""

3055384358.m_KeyValue: "Augustine thought for a moment. 'Did you enjoy yourselves today?'"

3055386526.m_KeyValue: ""'...Hmm?' Empousa lifted her head, and right at that moment, the seabird lowered its beak and pecked her nose tip with a light tap.""

3055386527.m_KeyValue: ""Back at the small wooden cabin where Tris was staying, Acappella curiously asked her, 'Commander, are you sure it's alright to let them have that debt note?'""

3055386530.m_KeyValue: ""'Stop spacing out, you dummy Empousa... the ball's falling!' Lamia anxiously watched the fish-skin ball plummeting from above. 'Servants, intercept that ball!'""

3055386531.m_KeyValue: ""Finally giving up her struggle, Acappella shrugged helplessly. 'Commander, I'm completely powerless here. It's all up to you now!'""

3055386532.m_KeyValue: "—Could all of this have been within Tris's calculations?"

3055386533.m_KeyValue: ""Empousa and Lamia stood motionless, at a loss for words—they finally realized they had been led by the nose from the very beginning...""

3055386535.m_KeyValue: ""'Take this! One! Strike! Victory!' High in the air, Lamia swung her leg in a full arc and kicked with tremendous force, sending the fish-skin ball rocketing toward the opposite court like a cannon shot, creating sonic booms in its wake.""

3055386536.m_KeyValue: "'You!' Empousa stomped her foot in anger. 'The Church is full of condescending bastards! What's so special about the Covenant?! Go ahead and use it—'"

3055386537.m_KeyValue: ""Just before touching the ground, the ball spent the last of its momentum. As it landed on the vine net, it created a deep arc in the mesh before suddenly springing high into the air—""

3062503601.m_KeyValue: ""One of the Bathory's surviving Elders, also the youngest. He seems to have some connection to the Cidhall family.""

3062503628.m_KeyValue:
"The manifestation of the Calamity _$$Famine_$$ in Hati's Spirit Realm.
It attempts to merge with Hati to reclaim its power."

3062724934.m_KeyValue: "These items might be treasures left by previous visitors. Please explore thoroughly."

3066792959.m_KeyValue: "You showed me that some things can transcend divides."

3066792960.m_KeyValue: ""You're the special one, Noah. You not only helped me find the organ, but when everyone else opposed me, you alone understood my wish to adopt Acappella and nurture her talent.""

3066792961.m_KeyValue: "You are the one who should be thanked for discovering a talent like Acappella."

3066792962.m_KeyValue: ""So today, you are not just a guest invited by a Bell Ringer. It's also a gesture of gratitude, from the choir and the Church, to you.""

3066792963.m_KeyValue: ""The Silver Blood keeps me from aging, while some of them have already entered their later years. Yet in my eyes, they are still children—in need of my care.""

3066792964.m_KeyValue: ""Then came Darcias, Acappella, and others. Decades have passed. Now, over forty children call this place home.""

3066792965.m_KeyValue: "I've indeed never met a Bell Ringer like you—one who adopts orphans and even welcomes a Bloodborn into the Church."

3066792966.m_KeyValue: ""Being a Bell Ringer is my divine duty, but the choir... it's my haven in this cruel world.""

3066792971.m_KeyValue: "Actually... this was another reason I invited you here."

3066792972.m_KeyValue: "You seem to take particular notice of Acappella."

3072815744.m_KeyValue: "We prepared some new clothes for you. I hope they fit."

3072815745.m_KeyValue: "I agree. It's better for him to experience it himself. I'll leave the next Embrace ritual to you."

3072815746.m_KeyValue: "The hungry want to eat and the sick want to get better. Are humans so different from the so-called 'vampires'?"

3075262940.m_KeyValue: ""Darcias's words made Acappella stop. After a few seconds of silence, she suddenly turned her head, her eyes turning completely white. 'EEEEEEK!'""

3077017787.m_KeyValue:
""In Bella's secret spot, I also found a notebook.

Inside, Bella had documented her studies of the ocean's tidal patterns, the moon's waxing and waning cycles, and the daily routines of life in Sapphire Isle... After uncovering all these patterns, Bella left her own assessment—dull.

It seems she expended every effort to understand this world, determined to uncover all its secrets.""

3077017853.m_KeyValue:
""The vision vanished without warning. In desperation, I drenched the Siren's Tear in every kind of liquor I had—At last, another glimpse.

Behind the prison bars, a masked guard slipped the maiden an envelope, saying: _$$From the Mysterious Merchant._$$

Could it be from her friend? Could that all-purpose Merchant truly deliver letters even into the depths of Hallon's prison?

For a moment, hope bloomed in her chest—

No. It was a command from the Master. A cruel snare, meant to make her a puppet. To force a choice between betraying her family or her friends. Throw it away. Tear it up.

But I could only stand outside the Siren's Tear, watching helplessly as it all unfolded.""

3077788336.m_KeyValue: ""Jestel eagerly crossed her fingers like a child: 'Quick, make a wish! Even though I'm the last of the Aegis line, I still hope there's a chance for our family to be reborn!'""

3077788339.m_KeyValue: ""'Actually, many ancient texts warn that shooting stars bring disaster!' Empousa declared with merciless glee!""

3077788341.m_KeyValue: ""'I'm going to search for that falling star we just witnessed! Who knows, I might be able to forge something extraordinary from it.'""

3146684755.m_KeyValue: "'The rest of the journal must be hidden there. Let's go!'"

3146684756.m_KeyValue: "So I gave myself wholly to the study of the moon."

3146684757.m_KeyValue: ""'Even you, heir to the Alita family, have no clue?'""

3146684758.m_KeyValue: ""Dragging Noah behind her, Empousa stepped into Aiona's room with concern. 'Aiona, how's the research coming along?'""

3146684761.m_KeyValue: "'Looks like I'll have to do it. No one's better at treasure hunts than me.'"

3146684762.m_KeyValue: "'Why do these notes look scorched? Were they burned?'"

3146685843.m_KeyValue: ""'Look—there's a note from the author: _$$After more than three years, I've finally brought this preliminary star-gazing journal to a close._$$'""

3146685844.m_KeyValue: ""The group gathered around Empousa, eyes fixed on the page in her hands.""

3146685845.m_KeyValue: ""'Is this… the moon?' Aiona held up a page from the journal, showing a page of black scribbles.""

3146685846.m_KeyValue: ""'We came to observe the moon,' Aiona explained gently.""

3146685849.m_KeyValue: ""'Next time you're moon-gazing, invite us too.'""

3146857907.m_KeyValue: ""...Hmm, looks like the second half of that sentence is on some other promotional material.""

3146857908.m_KeyValue: ""Baphomet paused, then snapped his gaze from the trophy to Gilrain. 'Gilrain Cidhall... Ha Ha Hahahaha!'""

3146857909.m_KeyValue: "As expected of the man known as the 'Soulless'—his words are lack any warmth."

3146857910.m_KeyValue: ""Hold on a second... It's a bit late to be asking this, but why is he called the Soulless? Wasn't this character supposed to be a soul that lost his physical body and is now attached to armor?""

3146857914.m_KeyValue: ""And last but not least... a warm welcome to our final attendee—whose seat is to the west, but who's currently sprawled to the north—the enigmatic and very cute black cat!""

3146858867.m_KeyValue: ""'A-Achoo!' Instead of a dignified response, Gilrain's ill-timed sneeze shatters the solemn atmosphere. His worsening cat allergy, it seems, has chosen a most inopportune moment to manifest.""

3146858868.m_KeyValue: ""As the trophy rolled back and forth between the cat's paws, Baphomet considered intervening, but was unwilling to lower himself to do so—""

3146858869.m_KeyValue: ""A deathly hush descended upon the scene, each person ruminating on Baphomet's words. Even the black cat quietly padded back to its seat, its eyes blinking with an expression that seemed to teeter between comprehension and bewilderment...""

3146858870.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey Gilrain, do be gentle, won't you? I have a hunch this intruder could become a big-time customer! And the silver hair... could it be the one Cain mentioned?'""

3146858871.m_KeyValue: ""Baphomet paused for a moment, then hefted his axe and lumbered forward as two spectral flames flickered to life within the void of his helmet. Through these flames, Gilrain and Bella seemed to glimpse something...""

3146897107.m_KeyValue: ""With a faint hiss, the candle flared to life, and at once came the clatter-clack of hidden mechanisms. The wall split open, revealing a narrow passage—just wide enough for one person to pass through.""

3146897108.m_KeyValue: "Seriously... what on earth has Van Helsing been teaching her?"

3146897109.m_KeyValue: ""Led by that hand, with the wind brushing her cheeks, Selena was guided toward the Infernal Kitchen—where she would spend one of the most blissful days of her summer.""

3146897110.m_KeyValue: ""Several months ago, at the Harbor of Soughs...""

3146897111.m_KeyValue: "'Because Lord Van Helsing once said...' Selena clenched her fists at her sides. 'Th-this outfit suits me—and he even patted my head... so gently...'"

3146897112.m_KeyValue: ""Bella offered no reply, meeting her gaze with a perfectly blank stare.""

3146897113.m_KeyValue: ""'That's the very purpose of our travels!' she declared, thrusting a finger forward with fiery conviction. 'Which is why we chose the Dekatres Archipelago, south of the Harbor of Soughs, as our first destination.'""

3146897114.m_KeyValue: ""'Hang in there! Whatever you do, don't fall asleep!' Selena clutched the girl's hand tighter as they ran beneath the blazing sun. 'Lord Van Helsing told me about cases like this...'""

3146897119.m_KeyValue: ""Bella gave no reply. But somewhere in that narrow, flickering space, fireflies rose like spirits from the dark—dancing softly around the two of them. And in the shifting light, something intangible seemed to bloom in the air.""

3146897120.m_KeyValue: ""From nowhere, a firefly emerged, circling lazily around Bella before drifting down to land upon the parchment. Its soft glow lit the surface and revealed a single line, written in bold—""

3146898197.m_KeyValue: ""Cain continued to explain, 'Put simply, it involves summoning the Matriarch's portrait through certain means, at a location far from her presence.'""

3146898199.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh? And will you claim that I'm also one of your creations, O illustrious Grand Alchemist?' The Matriarch's visage taunted.""

3146898200.m_KeyValue: ""'People often look at mirrors hoping to see the person they imagine themselves to be, only to be disappointed. But not when looking at these portraits.'""

3146898201.m_KeyValue: ""'The foretold day draws near,' Cain continued, his voice heavy with concern. 'Will you really disappear?'""

3146898202.m_KeyValue: "Lamia was the first to spot Cain and wasted no time in calling him out. 'Cain! Why are you loitering here instead of attending to your duties?'"

3146929783.m_KeyValue: "'Enough!' Baphomet cut in sharply. 'What I want to discuss is how we can create more powerful vessels to counter the growing strength of other powerful families.'"

3146929784.m_KeyValue: ""'Let us commence our monthly Elder meeting,' Baphomet, in his capacity as Chief Elder, declared. 'Our agenda today concerns the recent Blood conflicts among other families.'""

3146929785.m_KeyValue: ""'That's right,' Gilrain declared, laying bare his true feelings. 'If anyone's to be compared to the Lion, it should be us, the Bull. The Horse doesn't even deserve to be mentioned in the same breath!'""

3146929786.m_KeyValue: ""'However, obtaining their ancestral blood would likely require venturing into the forbidden grounds, and that Gravekeeper Clive Ganelon is no pushover.'""

3147001656.m_KeyValue: ""However, as in many clichéd tales, one Ancestor fell for the girl. He soon noticed some of his fellow Ancestrals struggling more and more to suppress their growing hunger.""

3147001657.m_KeyValue: ""It's said that during the Crimson Inquisition, several Ancestors with unique Blood Powers hid in the vault, along with some prisoners of war.'""

3147001658.m_KeyValue: ""Upon infiltrating, however, they found that guarding the vault's entrance was neither a powerful seal nor a terrifying monster—but an elderly man with a large key ring dangling from his waist.""

3147002611.m_KeyValue: ""To help set the mood more vividly, we should clarify their positions:""

3147002612.m_KeyValue: ""Darkness consumed the room. Even though all three had faced far worse before… In that moment, a quiet, inexplicable dread began to stir in each of their hearts.""

3147002613.m_KeyValue: ""Whatever had been lurking in the darkness loosened its grip on Bella's arm. But no one was foolish enough to believe it had left. That overwhelming presence, driven by an obsession so dense it nearly took form, still pressed down upon them...""

3147002614.m_KeyValue: ""Fresh cuts of Raog can be prepared in a variety of ways, though the most celebrated are the Raog Belly Sashimi and the Glasflare Fin Soup served at the Infernal Kitchen of Harbor of Soughs.""

3147002616.m_KeyValue: ""'…Rest assured, Lady Empousa. This is for the sake of…'""

3147002617.m_KeyValue: ""'Right—gracing our humble estate. We, uh… regret not seeing you off properly…'""

3147002618.m_KeyValue: ""'The Bathory ancestors left behind... certain inexplicable remnants. Strange occurrences like this are, unfortunately, not uncommon here.'""

3147002623.m_KeyValue: ""'So… this was all your doing, wasn't it?' Lorelei fixed Bella with a half-smile, half-glare. 'I'm guessing… there'll be even more theatrical horrors waiting in the Ancestral Vault?'""

3147002624.m_KeyValue: ""Well—depending on how you looked at it, maybe that's what you'd call a fair exchange.""

3164136258.m_KeyValue:
""After falling from the cliff of Starfall Valley, I was rescued by Aiona and Empousa. By the campfire that night, Aiona handed me a small lamb craft and told me there was still a future worth pursuing. Only now do I understand why she felt so strangely familiar, why she stayed by my side as I searched for my identity.

That night, in the flickering firelight, she said: _$$I will witness your future, just as you once accompanied me._$$""

3164324320.m_KeyValue: ""Until that day, when I was about to leave and several bats suddenly appeared before me.""

3164324321.m_KeyValue: ""If you were constantly compared to your _$$sister_$$ from birth, knowing that only by surpassing her could you survive, you'd develop the same instinct.""

3164324322.m_KeyValue: ""A sudden evening breeze swept in, carrying the hair ornament I had given to Lamia into the night sky.""

3164324323.m_KeyValue: "What she wanted to give me wasn't a weapon..."

3174672496.m_KeyValue:
""I hear the voice at the end of time—
Like the ancient strings at the dawn of the world,
Like the soft murmur of all living things.
The river flows from that far shore,
On this side, it nurtures will, memory, and civilization;
On the Other Side, it nurtures the sun, stars, and moon.
Aeon takes my hand as we sail on the river,
On the left, the clamor of iron forges and silhouettes of travelers,
On the right, the loneliness of home and the morning stars of the night.
I shall Embark from this shore,
Taking Aeon's hand, to journey towards the Other Side.""

3174802881.m_KeyValue: ""Unforgivable heretic of the Bloodborn, prepare to face judgment.""

3177077089.m_KeyValue: "My parents' faces blurred. Their voices grew faint. The bedtime stories they told me scattered into fragments."

3177077090.m_KeyValue: ""According to the dictionary, your behavior would be described as unusual.""

3177938756.m_KeyValue: ""Kid, don't rope me in unless it's vital. I'd rather catch some more shut-eye.""

3179716967.m_KeyValue: "What are your thoughts on 'adhering to family-first policy in all matters'?"

3179720038.m_KeyValue: "What are your thoughts on 'continuing to uphold the principle of the First Tenet of Secrecy'?"

3192212480.m_KeyValue: ""At his zenith, Dracula devised a technique to consummate the Bloodborn around the world, sharing his blood with vassals to make them as formidable as himself. When the Bathory family took power, they found that this technique worked not just for Bloodborn, but any young person, granting them the ability to transfuse blood from their ancestors. Perhaps… all life shares a common origin, after all?""

3223869066.m_KeyValue: ""After Ami fused with the Calamity _$$Famine,_$$ she became the true ruler of the deep sea. This marks her new form's first venture onto land.""

3223869074.m_KeyValue: ""Claims to be from an organization named the _$$Silver Cross,_$$ which operates under the Tempus Church. He regards commitment to justice as his highest mission.""

3223869076.m_KeyValue: ""One of the Church's Twelve Bell Ringers, she manages the Chamber of War. Believing war can solve all conflicts, she is known as the Goddess of War.""

3236574978.m_KeyValue:
""The carefully stored hymn robe and sheet music bear witness to the turning point in Acappella's life. She's complained to me about many boring things, but never about singing.

Perhaps only when she's softly singing hymns does the world quiet down to listen to her voice.

Now, my ears too are filled with Acappella's thoughts and worries.

Somewhere along the way, this shared cacophony has gradually been brightened by a young girl's cheerful laughter.""

3236575226.m_KeyValue: ""Empousa remembers the day Aiona suddenly agreed to forge a new ritual tool. She said a mysterious friend had encouraged her. Empousa was overjoyed. That day, Aiona handed her damaged tool to Empousa. She said something strange: _$$The tool had no reason to carry my longing for the past or my defiance of the future._$$ Under the clear sky, she decided it was time to start anew.""

3243551870.m_KeyValue: ""I'd say that's a fair call, all things considered.""

3243557249.m_KeyValue: ""If this path leads to greater strength, then you have my support.""

3243558404.m_KeyValue: ""It must be done, in this way.""

3244846946.m_KeyValue: ""Crows that soar above Starfall Valley. After being infected with Black Blood outside the sealed area, the explosive power of their crystalline form reached its limit. Upon death, crystal shards explode from their bodies in a wide swath.""

3244847034.m_KeyValue: "A priest warped by the Black Blood. The defilement of their sacred scriptures has transformed their spells into twisted curses."

3244847035.m_KeyValue: ""A knight grotesquely twisted under the influence of Black Blood. Devoid of faith, their swordsmanship is now tempered by pure insanity.""

3244847044.m_KeyValue: "An unmistakably canid-like creature discovered in Lupine Forest. Its exaggerated spine implies a body terribly distorted."

3244847046.m_KeyValue: ""A peasant residing near the Lupine Forest. The Black Blood infection stripped away their sanity, leaving only a blood-covered scythe as a testament to their madness.""

3244847047.m_KeyValue: ""An unmistakably canid-like creature discovered in Lupine Forest. This creature has lost all semblance of its original form, becoming a monstrous beast.""

3244847048.m_KeyValue: ""A hunter residing near the Lupine Forest. Despite their infection with Black Blood, their archery skills retain a deadly precision.""

3244847049.m_KeyValue: ""A hunter residing near the Lupine Forest. Despite their infection with Black Blood, their archery skills retain a deadly precision.""

3247415522.m_KeyValue: ""Isn't that too severe? Preserving progeny is crucial for the family's revival. Why don't we reduce the severity of punishments? For instance, we could remove 'Exile' and 'Execution' as options.""

3247415619.m_KeyValue: ""Come to think of it, why doesn't Cain ever collaborate with other alchemists in his research?""

3247415786.m_KeyValue: ""The Observatory holds special significance for our family. It was established to observe the Other Side of the Moon. From the changes in the stars, we can read many omens. We should repair it as soon as possible. We mustn't delay such important matters!""

3247415852.m_KeyValue: ""A vassal's worthiness of our respect should not be determined by their origin, but by their actions within our castle.""

3247415918.m_KeyValue: ""I remember that description of the 'Other Side'! 'Time in the Other Side flows parallel to our reality, its space intertwines with our own. The secret of 'eternal life' may be hidden within.'""

3247415949.m_KeyValue: ""They say these 'Future Artifacts' don't belong to this era, but for some reason, they were misplaced on this continent. Hmm... there must be more to this story!""

3247415984.m_KeyValue: ""I've noticed that even the alchemical ingredients they use are quite unusual. Things like mistletoe, beryl...""

3247416015.m_KeyValue: "It's definitely worth a try! Alchemy can not only enhance our Blood power but also create various everyday items!"

3247416081.m_KeyValue: ""These meteor fragments look completely unremarkable, and according to our family's senior alchemist, they cannot be refined into anything useful.""

3252650298.m_KeyValue: "It seems you attacked us in the depths of the forbidden grounds to protect Hati before she was even born."

3252650299.m_KeyValue: ""_$$To be honest, I used to feel so frustrated. Finally gaining power only to discover that those I wanted to protect were already gone._$$""

3252650300.m_KeyValue: "It seems Noah has already delivered my message to him."

3252650301.m_KeyValue: "_$$The chains_$$... So that's what it meant?"

3254159654.m_KeyValue: "Consider this tale the price of a drink. What I want to know is the _$$seventh tale_$$ of Bell Ringer Agares Brennholt."

3254159655.m_KeyValue: "The price of a drink... Those words remind me of someone dear—the Second Princess of Carrelle. The one who died with me in the fire."

3254159656.m_KeyValue: "We're getting off track. Why don't we try interpreting the _$$five decrees_$$ and _$$six wings_$$ together..."

3254159657.m_KeyValue: "Hm? What's this? You're in the mood to buy me a drink?"

3254159658.m_KeyValue: ""_$$Seven drops of blood to stir what's yet ahead, and death shall be the place he makes his bed._$$""

3254159660.m_KeyValue: "She was quite the drinker... Tell me—among those _$$ghosts_$$ who told you stories about me... Was she one of them?"

3269299581.m_KeyValue:
""The rest of the story is likely familiar to all.

She descended like an arrow loosed from its bow. Like Death's bat servant, she landed at the coachman's neck.

_$$The moon is but a dream of the sun, and thus we were forgotten by the light._$$

She was beautiful as she sang at the cliff's edge, yet her song etched an eternal question in the hearts of those who heard.

When someone vanishes, are they erased from the world? I'm not certain, but I know I will remember her from tonight.

My answer seemed to move her. Before the stake, she sank her fangs into my neck and took my blood.

My vision turned scarlet, just like the flowers in her basket. I wonder if my answer helped resolve her doubts.""

3316464741.m_KeyValue: ""Noah: Thank you. Without all of you, I might have remained asleep forever, sealed within that little puppet. Tell Miss Ami that I believe she will make a fine Sage. Tell Miss Aiona that I'm grateful for her gentleness and kindness. Tell Miss Selena that I wish we could've watched Ginokio together one more time. While I slept, Sapphire Isle became a place I no longer recognized. But after meeting all of you, I came to love what it's become. If fate allowed, I would've gladly gone on another journey with you. But there's a promise I must keep. Lorelei is still waiting for me. They say a letter lets you glimpse someone's truest thoughts. So if you've read this far... I suppose you know this is my last letter. The money enclosed should be enough to buy a few Tidewisp seeds. Please plant them by the sea for me. That's my last request.""

3338533693.m_KeyValue: ""The young think far too simplistically. Allow me to speak on behalf of the Elders: Though the family shows signs of rising prominence, we must remain cautious and maintain a prudent distance from the Kingdom and the Church.""

3338533759.m_KeyValue: ""Hold on, hold on. I've learned that this chamber is located at the border between the Ganelon and Carrelle territories. Although its position is secluded, there's still a risk of it being seized.""

3338533790.m_KeyValue: ""The elders rack their brains night after night for the future of our family. And now, they're expected to let a bunch of brats decide how well-done their steaks should be and how soft their beds are...""

3338533825.m_KeyValue: ""Developing trade routes takes time and resources, but that's a matter for later. The family is at a crucial stage of revival. Castle repairs, cultivating vassals, the 'Return to the Moon' project... everything requires Soli.""

3338533856.m_KeyValue: ""The young are quick to judge what they scarcely understand. Though the First Tenet of Secrecy was indeed established during the Bathory's decline, its true purpose is to ensure the utmost preservation of our bloodline.""

3338533891.m_KeyValue: ""How naive! Since the Holy War, the Church has all but eradicated Black Blood from the continent. The Bloodborn barely survived—another Bloodborn faction’s existence is impossible.""

3338533922.m_KeyValue: "No intention of getting involved? What a joke! I've never seen such cowardly Bloodborn! Bathory would never stoop so low as to ally with such a conservative and weak faction!"

3338533988.m_KeyValue: ""Hold on! Bathory Castle is no refuge for strays! As the Lord himself said, the Bathory and Ganelon families have been sworn enemies for generations—how could we possibly take their descendants as our Vassals?""

3338534023.m_KeyValue: ""I was the first to object when the Elder Baphomet decided to purchase armor from her. Now look where we are—not only are prices soaring, but the Puppet Association has monopolized all business in the castle. In my opinion, it's high time we take measures to regulate this situation.""

3338534120.m_KeyValue: ""We must remain vigilant. The cartographers may claim neutrality, but persistent rumors suggest that several of its members frequently accept missions from the Church, operating in their service.""

3374585011.m_KeyValue:
""'Thank you, Dr. Ressa.'
The elderly woman before me bowed repeatedly in her gratitude.
Though I've lost count of how many patients I've treated today, her smile still gave me a glimmer of strength.
For years, I've done my utmost to help these patients in remote villages.
'Why do you go to such lengths, Dr. Ressa?' the old woman asked before she left.
Why indeed...
Is it because of the horrors of war I've experienced, and the fear of death they instilled in me?
Or is it guilt over the lives taken, driving me to cherish it above all else?
I do not know. But now, all I want is to keep everyone as far from death as possible, no matter the toll it takes on me—
After all, only this makes me feel truly alive.""

""A complex mechanical device.
Inspired by an engineer's nightmare, some speculated he dreamed of hellfire raining from the sky.
In fact, it was just a dream about complicated parabolic formulas.""

3411471170.m_KeyValue: ""A silver sword forgotten by time and space. The blood crusted on its hilt speaks of Noah's glorious victories as the _$$Bloodborn hunter_$$ for the Church. In another life, would he still suffer from doubt, or yearn for an unreachable homeland—even if he no longer dwelled in the shadow of the sun?""

3411471171.m_KeyValue: ""A shield forgotten by time and space. Its twisted design was once hailed by the _$$great weaponsmith_$$ Jestel as a work of rare artistry. In another life, would she still recall the tale of the Moonblessed, and share it with her kin?""

3411471172.m_KeyValue: ""A bouquet forgotten by time and space. Planting carnations among piles of bones was the wish of Empousa, the _$$new leader of the family._$$ In another life, would she wonder how fate might have shifted, had she dared venture into Starfall Valley that night?""

3411471173.m_KeyValue: ""Observation equipment forgotten by time and space. _$$The observer of time,_$$ Aiona, has worn through thousands like it. In another life, would she abandon her obsession with the end of time—and consider leaving the Alita family to seek a different sky?""

3411471174.m_KeyValue: ""A flaming bow forgotten by time and space. Its charred surface bears witness to the _$$new Bell Ringer_$$ Setti’s mastery of fire. In another life, would she have questioned her teacher’s true intentions that night in Starfall Valley, after taking Agares's place?""

3411471175.m_KeyValue: ""Seafaring gourmet foods forgotten by time and space. The writhing tentacles on the platter are trophies from Ami, _$$Captain of the El Dorado,_$$ taken from the deep. In another life, would she still yearn for the land while bound to the helm—or would the sea and storm, at last, feel like home?""

3411471176.m_KeyValue: ""Bones forgotten by time and space. Precisely modified and fused with the body of Cecia, the _$$Ascendant._$$ In another life, having refused to be her family's sacrifice, would she have found her true self in flesh and metal?""

3411471177.m_KeyValue: ""A music box forgotten by time and space. The little girl dancing atop it glows like _$$Lady_$$ Bella herself. In another life, as pure flesh and blood, would she care about if the puppet in the box had a soul?""

3411471178.m_KeyValue: ""A staff forgotten by time and space. The snake coiled atop has guided countless lost souls with Cain, the _$$guide to the Other Side._$$ In another life, when he walked the world of the living, would things have turned out differently for Cain had he finished that chess game at the Demon Banquet?""

3411473345.m_KeyValue: ""Sharp fangs, often crafted into amulets. Said to drain power from enemies when worn.""

3411473348.m_KeyValue: ""A deep grayish ore, symbolizing death through its lethal toxicity. Yet to alchemists, this very power of destruction holds the potential for new life.""

3411474369.m_KeyValue: ""A peculiar device prone to sudden explosions. In the wrong hands, the consequences are unthinkable.""

3411474372.m_KeyValue:
""A complex mechanical device.
Inspired by an engineer's nightmare, some speculated he dreamed of hellfire raining from the sky.
In fact, it was just a dream about complicated parabolic formulas.""

3430728059.m_KeyValue: "I saw the perpetual worry etched on my clan members' faces as the sea levels continued to rise."

3430728066.m_KeyValue: "That fish took quite a bit of effort to catch. It's rare to find one bigger than you."

3430728068.m_KeyValue: ""By the way, one of the fish in the kitchen was an incarnation of Calamity. That one didn't taste very good.""

3430728069.m_KeyValue: ""Yes, it's quite a rare scent indeed.""

3430728070.m_KeyValue: ""Actually, I can gain certain memories, or rather, sensations, by consuming food.""

3430728071.m_KeyValue: "That's why it could summon you through the conch shell—they're both creatures of the sea."

3430728073.m_KeyValue: ""But the fish in the kitchen didn't have any meaningful memories for me to see, so I had to ask you to catch some bigger ones.""

3435365707.m_KeyValue:
""A vessel filled with blood. Use to exchange for Divine Blood Drops, based on your Moonlight Faith LV.
<alpha=#80>From the stars we were born, yet now we gaze at them from afar.""

3435365709.m_KeyValue:
""A box full of Soli. Use to exchange for Soli equal to the yield in the specific ritual time (based on Moonlight Faith level).
<alpha=#80>Even creatures of the night find solace in the allure of material riches.""

3435365710.m_KeyValue:
""A vessel full of Pure Blood Essence. Use to exchange for Pure Blood Essence equals to the yield in the specific ritual time (based on Moonlight Faith level).
<alpha=#80>Its deep crimson hues give onlookers an unsettling feeling.""

3436045291.m_KeyValue: ""When the battle begins and every 10 sec after, grants a Shield equal to <style=""Highlight"">{0}</style> of Starry-Eyed Aiona's Max HP to the ally deployed on the tile, lasting for {1} sec.""

3436177592.m_KeyValue: "Deals strong DMG to all enemies in a select area."

3436354461.m_KeyValue: "Is that even up for debate? It's the obvious course of action. Only a fool would think otherwise!"

3436355484.m_KeyValue: "I'm in! Just follow me and we can't fail!"

3436356639.m_KeyValue: ""With 'The Chariot' at our disposal, we can boldly forge ahead.""

3436357662.m_KeyValue: "I appreciate this flexibility. It gives us strategic options."

3436657333.m_KeyValue:
""Soul Shards collected by the undertaker. Collect 50 of them for a chance to obtain Ancestral Vassals.
<alpha=#80>_$$When paths cross, it is destiny's design._$$""

3436657364.m_KeyValue:
""Soul Shards collected by the undertaker. Collect 50 of them to Embrace SR/SSR Vassals.
<alpha=#80>Notes from the undertaker's journal: _$$A gentle soul that refused to submit to the Holy Flame._$$""

3436661427.m_KeyValue: ""Have no worry. All will settle into place, like dust after a storm.""

3438177941.m_KeyValue: "Increases ATK and M. DEF of Ancestral Vassals."

3439704775.m_KeyValue: ""Whether it's the first 'special type' we rescued from the Church, or Lady Empousa...""

3439709991.m_KeyValue: "But it's strange... why haven't they arrived after all this time..."

3447992322.m_KeyValue: "The caster heals the carrier based on the carrier's Max HP every sec. Does not stack with effects of the same type."

3447992324.m_KeyValue: ""When dealing DMG, CRIT Rate +{0}. Does not stack with effects of the same type.""

3447992325.m_KeyValue: "CRIT DMG Taken -{0}. Does not stack with effects of the same type."

3447992327.m_KeyValue: "P. DMG Taken -{0}. Does not stack with effects of the same type."

3453645605.m_KeyValue: "Do not lament or frown upon failure."

3453645667.m_KeyValue:
""The bloodstained night was my final resting place.
With my remaining strength, I crawled towards her, curling up beside her cold body.
Through the mirror of congealed blood, I saw two identical faces.""

3454329443.m_KeyValue: ""Baphomet's power ignites the Battlefield, continuously dealing True DMG to all enemies. Units who receive HP recovery effects become immune to this effect for a period of time.""

3457719671.m_KeyValue: ""Every {0} sec, summons a Phoenix that deals <style=""Highlight"">{1}</style> ATK (M. DMG) to one random target. For each Continuous DMG effect gained by enemies, the cooldown on Agares' Special is reduced by 1 sec, up to a maximum of 5 sec.""

3458272617.m_KeyValue: ""Gilrain scrutinized the tattered linen in his hands. 'This peculiar pattern, reminiscent of an eye... I've scoured every record in the Church's archives, yet found no mention of it anywhere.'""

3458272618.m_KeyValue: ""As they emerged from the depths of the forest, the mist faded away. The trio were left with the bittersweet sensation of awakening from a shared dream.""

3458272619.m_KeyValue: "'I advise you to be more careful—' Gilrain's warning was cut short as misfortune struck."

3458272620.m_KeyValue: ""'You just made me think of something,' Gilrain said, his eyes darting between the similar yet distinct patterns on two manuscripts.""

3458275881.m_KeyValue: ""The cat sat up straight and twirled its right paw through the air. Overhead, the floating Tarot cards responded at once, swirling into a gentle shuffle. 'The crystal ball? Just a tool for fortune-telling, meow.'""

3458275882.m_KeyValue: ""Joan's fighting spirit felt as if it could take form—And in that very instant, the tent flap stirred without a breeze. Was this the power of a Bell Ringer? A will so intense it could bend the air around it?""

3458275883.m_KeyValue: ""The crystal ball spun with a gentle clink as it rolled off the edge… Thankfully, it landed in a patch of grass near the entrance without a scratch. Was that... planned?""

3458275884.m_KeyValue: ""And why suspicious (repeated twice, no less)? Because what kind of fortune-teller sets up shop in the middle of nowhere!?""

3458275885.m_KeyValue: ""It's Dalcarlo, of course! Who else in all of Minexus is known for her skill in Tarot divination?""

3458275887.m_KeyValue: ""Theophane picked up the card, studied it for a moment, then slapped it face-down on the table. '...Draw again,' he said, his voice low and firm with resolve.""

3458275888.m_KeyValue: "'Let's set that aside for now.' Joan waved her hand. 'You mentioned a contest in fortune-telling... How exactly do we determine who's better at that?'"

3458275892.m_KeyValue: ""'To recover the stolen ceremonial relic…' Halfway through his sentence, he paused, then frowned. 'Wait... The crystal ball?'""

3458343401.m_KeyValue: ""Agares halted at those words, a fleeting trace of sorrow crossing his face—only to vanish the next instant.""

3458343402.m_KeyValue: "'Not many Bell Ringers have this much free time...' Noah let out a weary smile. 'No wonder you've gone through so many Vice-Commanders. They're not exactly fans of a leader who always shirks his duties.'"

3458343403.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh...? Ah, I see...' Noah took another small step back. 'So... whatever this is, it hasn't been buried long?'""

3458343404.m_KeyValue: ""Noah peered down into the pit from above, meeting Agares's gaze. As their eyes met, the same thought surfaced in their minds...""

3458343405.m_KeyValue: ""Agares chuckled and shook his head. 'The moment you said let's settle this, you'd already lost.'""

3458343406.m_KeyValue: ""'Hey now, that's my line.' Twin Agares lets out an exasperated sigh. 'Can't believe even my day off comes with this kind of trouble...'""

3458343407.m_KeyValue: ""At that question, Mass lowered her head slightly. 'Just a phantom shaped like Agares. A vessel for the countless lingering wills of the Carrelle family.'""

3458343408.m_KeyValue: "'You both spoke in third person when you were making your arguments.' Noah stared intently at the two identical men before him. 'Like you were talking about someone else.'"

3458343410.m_KeyValue: ""'...This meteorite seems to draw in the lingering souls of the nearby Carrelle dead.' Mass turned back. 'When these fragments, glimmering like firelies, gather together...'""

3458344489.m_KeyValue: ""Acappella even closed her eyes to focus on listening, but why did the distractions become even clearer?""

3458344491.m_KeyValue: ""The stone door, bearing the Badge of the Bathory family, rumbled deeply as the stenchy cold air escaped through the gap like desperate wraiths.""

3458344492.m_KeyValue: ""'Indeed, this isn't how a Covenant should be used. But on the bright side, I survived.'""

3458344493.m_KeyValue: ""'I don't know either, it just suddenly came to my head.'""

3458344496.m_KeyValue: "'I told you! Don't touch my receiver!'"

3458344499.m_KeyValue: ""'Aca-aca, pella-pella.' This time she added some dance moves to the rhythm.""

3458344500.m_KeyValue: ""'You're no fun at all! Let's go.' As Acappella turned to leave, she casually snapped her fingers, reducing the mud monster behind her to ashes in an instant.""

3458399101.m_KeyValue: ""Act carefully during the heist, avoiding direct confrontation with Artifact Guards unless necessary. Engaging in battle increases their Alert level, and defeat will result in immediate failure.""

3458416361.m_KeyValue: ""'I can't believe the old man would stoop to such tricks,' Clive thought. In his mind, that distant father had always been the embodiment of righteousness and loyalty.""

3458416362.m_KeyValue: "'Neither of us. Our contests always ended prematurely for various reasons. And I never had another chance to compete with your father.'"

3458416365.m_KeyValue: ""'Watch your opponent's rhythm,' Gadric instructed calmly, his movements fluid as he deftly dodged and retreated.""

3458416366.m_KeyValue: ""'Well, well,' he mused, 'it seems even the most seasoned warrior can falter. Fortunate this wasn't a real battle.' With Hati's aid, he sat up on the smooth rocks.""

3458416367.m_KeyValue: ""'I haven't even crossed swords with every knight, how could I possibly claim to be the first among them? Even if I've won once, I might lose the second time.'""

3458416368.m_KeyValue: ""Clive lent a hand, slicing the bread, cheese, and ham to prepare their meal.""

3458419628.m_KeyValue: ""'But...' Hati suddenly murmured, her voice barely audible, 'Was the sacrifice of those Ganelons truly meaningful?'""

3458419629.m_KeyValue: "'The Ganelons in the tower began firing arrows. Anyone who charged the entrance was either shot dead or cut down by a Ganelon defender at the doorway.'"

3458419630.m_KeyValue: ""'Well, of course. The Aegis family took part in that battle too. But it's not really something to be proud of, is it?'""

3458419631.m_KeyValue: ""Empousa and Jestel joined Hati at the edge. Together, the three stood silently, letting the salty sea breeze caress their faces as they watched the waves crash rhythmically against the distant shore.""

3458419632.m_KeyValue: ""'Your family's domain?' Hati scoffed, her anger barely contained. 'Fangtooth Tower belongs to the Ganelon family.'""

3458447946.m_KeyValue: ""'A wise decision,' Cain nodded approvingly. 'If you're seeking specific texts, perhaps I can... guide your search.'""

3458447947.m_KeyValue: ""Undaunted by the overwhelming odds, the trio spread out with trained precision. Like young lions on the hunt, they silently stalked their formidable prey.""

3458447948.m_KeyValue: ""'Even with its proximity to the Bathory's castle,' Isaac persisted in his pessimism, 'this site couldn't have escaped the attention of clandestine looters.'""

3458447952.m_KeyValue: ""'The goddess, in her infinite wisdom, not only blessed the devout follower with a mighty warrior for a son, but also thoughtfully hastened his growth to adulthood.'""

3458448905.m_KeyValue: ""(One always wears a mask for who-knows-what reason, the other's constantly trying to slack off… How did they end up as Bell Ringers?)""

3458448906.m_KeyValue: ""Seriously… these are supposed to be the Church's top fighters? Where's the dignity of a Bell Ringer? If word got out that they spend their time playing hide-and-seek, how would the Church live it down?""

3458448907.m_KeyValue: ""Agares also stopped, glancing in the same direction. 'Oh…?'""

3458448908.m_KeyValue: ""'Ooh, look at this blood-red vertical eye… Doesn't it remind you of those Bloodborn?'""

3458448909.m_KeyValue: ""'Naming stuff's my specialty!' Acappella tilted her head, deep in thought. 'Since it was found under a rock on a quiet path, let's call it…'""

3458448910.m_KeyValue: ""He suddenly paused mid-sentence, then gave a soft chuckle. 'Heh. So that's what this is… a trap.' Shoulders lifting in resignation, he muttered, '…skip.'""

3458448911.m_KeyValue: ""With flair, Acappella raised the card (Bell Ringer–only) dramatically above her head—Then smacked it down to the ground with a 'Slap'!""

3458448912.m_KeyValue: ""'I offer six cards from my hand…' Crossing his arms before him, Agares clenched his fists. Between each pair of fingers, a card (Bell Ringer–only) gleamed faintly.""

3458448913.m_KeyValue: ""Before any of the three Bell Ringers could react, she swiftly tossed something their way—And with perfect aim, the objects landed straight into their mouths. Looking closer... they were those strange mushrooms from earlier.""

3458488235.m_KeyValue: ""'Was it for the money, or to fulfill that contract?' You've probably never seen a tree scratching its head with its own branches.""

3458488236.m_KeyValue: ""'This journey may span three or four generations to complete, with the plants along the way serving as vital waystations for their journey.'""

3458488237.m_KeyValue: ""'He lay in wait outside the prison gates for days, finally finding a few recently released inmates with nowhere else to turn.'""

3458488238.m_KeyValue: ""Yggdrasill accepted the tea from his disciple with his wounded branch, seemingly using this gesture to show his displeasure. Then again, it's not exactly easy to read emotions on a tree, is it?""

3458488239.m_KeyValue: ""'Then I'll find a big tree!' Edina exclaimed. Her hands trembled, the realization of her near mistake hitting her suddenly.""

3458488240.m_KeyValue: ""'I have no interest in human affairs,' Yggdrasill stated flatly. If not for his disciple, he wouldn't have set foot in this waystation at all.""

3458519817.m_KeyValue: ""Without warning, Empousa hitched up her skirt and darted off. 'The race is on!'""

3458519818.m_KeyValue: ""Wordlessly, Hati approached the edge of the wheat field. She reached out, grasping an ear of golden wheat. As she gently rubbed it between her fingers, brown grains slipped through the gaps.""

3458519821.m_KeyValue: ""'Couldn't they just buy food?' Ami asked, bewildered. Her experience observing Goldland doing business made this situation utterly incomprehensible.""

3458519822.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh Ami, of course you wouldn't understand, having spent your life at sea,' Empousa said with an air of superiority. 'A mill needs regular cleaning, otherwise it becomes a haven for rats and insects.'""

3458519823.m_KeyValue: ""'No wonder this isn't mentioned in the Bathory family records,' Empousa exclaimed. 'We inadvertently cultivated such a powerful enemy for ourselves—it's utterly humiliating!'""

3458519824.m_KeyValue: ""'But weren't the Ganelon family worried that the Bathory family might sabotage the flour?' Ami asked, though she already knew how it had turned out.""

3458525131.m_KeyValue: "'Yup' Hati beamed with joy. 'It's my very first pair of boxing gloves! Father made them for me using Clive's old clothes.'"

3458525132.m_KeyValue: "'Mouret is going to be completely abandoned. I should let this glove stay here with my other treasured one.'"

3458525133.m_KeyValue: ""'It's just... I've never been this close to lightning in the open before, and... and...'""

3458525134.m_KeyValue: ""'That's rather perplexing,' Ressa mused. 'Wouldn't an architect of such renown have incorporated safeguards against such disasters?'""

3458525135.m_KeyValue: ""This continued until all the wheat had been ground into flour and transported back to the Bathory lands. Empousa and Ressa, meanwhile, were there purely for the excitement.""

3458525136.m_KeyValue: ""'With three people, it's really quite straightforward,' Hati said, leaving the other two completely baffled.""

3458591689.m_KeyValue: "'I’ve been wanting to say this all along... There are hot springs all over this island. Couldn’t everyone just use a different one? What was the point of fighting over this?'"

3458591690.m_KeyValue: ""The bear submerged itself, leaving only its head above water. With practiced ease, it placed the still-trembling squirrel on its forehead like a compress, wearing an expression of pure bliss.""

3458591691.m_KeyValue: ""'Allow me to explain in detail...' Agares raised a finger, as if fully prepared to educate these amateurs on the fine art of crafting a proper hot spring.""

3458591692.m_KeyValue: "'What a hassle... no one's even listening to me.'"

3458591693.m_KeyValue: ""'Oh, I get it—' Hati nodded along then froze. 'Wait...'""

3458591694.m_KeyValue: ""'This is awful! Did we get here too late? The legendary hot spring has been tainted!' Hati slumped her shoulders in frustration, radiating an aura of utter dejection.""

3458591695.m_KeyValue: ""'...Should I get down and apologize? Wait, why me?'""

3458591696.m_KeyValue: ""Hati dashed to the ship’s railing, vomiting before her words could even finish. It seemed that even after transforming from a clumsy wolf into a moth, she hadn’t shaken her predisposition to seasickness.""

3458592650.m_KeyValue: ""'An empty shell without flesh?' Darcias studied the cross-section of the helmet, answering idly, 'Like that elder from a certain noble house who passed away not long ago?'""

3458592651.m_KeyValue: ""Nicole flexed the legs she'd formed with mercury manipulation. 'With all this mist, it's like I've filled the area with eyes and copies of myself.'""

3458592653.m_KeyValue: "'Ah... what brings you here?' Gadric changed the subject. 'I don't see your Bell Ringer. It's rare for a Vice-Commander to appear alone.'"

3458592654.m_KeyValue: ""With a loud splash, a second _$$unexpected guest_$$ popped up from beneath the surface. Was she lying in wait this whole time?""

3458592655.m_KeyValue: ""Let’s hope she and her Vassal are getting along, and that a little cliff-diving hasn't driven a wedge between them.""

3458592656.m_KeyValue: ""'Just as you predicted.' Darcias circled the floating Gadric, scrutinizing him. 'But how did you pull it off? There's no way he'd drown that easily.'""

3458592661.m_KeyValue: ""'Ahahaha!' Gadric burst into hearty laughter, like a child after a successful prank. 'Darcias fell for another one!'""

3458663569.m_KeyValue: ""'As we agreed earlier, I'm with Goldland, while you, Silver-haired, are paired with Cain. Hmph, remember, you chose this pairing yourself, Silver-haired! So don't come fishing for excuses if you end up on the losing side!'""

3458663570.m_KeyValue: ""As the thin mist dissipated, the the object was revealed—a golden hourglass. What set this timepiece apart, however, was the intricate carving of a man upon its surface.""

3458663571.m_KeyValue: "Noah froze at this shocking revelation—'Smuggling seafood?'"

3458663573.m_KeyValue: ""Goldland had Noah by the head while Cain gripped his hands, each yanking in opposite directions. All the while, they were yelling 'Seafood Tycoon's Pearl!' at the top of their lungs.""

3458663574.m_KeyValue: ""'Precisely,' Cain said, raising the golden hourglass high. 'Now, chant with me: Come forth, Seafood Tycoon Pearl!'""

3458663575.m_KeyValue: ""...And thus, amidst a whirlwind of chaos, the Greatest Fishing Competition of the Minexus drew to its chaotic yet successful conclusion. We extend our heartfelt thanks to the Golden Goldland Statue for its unwavering support of this... memorable event.""

3458663576.m_KeyValue: ""The remaining three locked eyes, exchanging silent nods of understanding. Their hands—all six of them—curled into white-knuckled fists as their minds raced with visions of grand conquests and glorious empires. True warriors, after all, do not falter in the face of mere setbacks!""

3458665745.m_KeyValue: "'Surely we didn't all come here just to trade words?' Tris smiled as she swept her gaze across everyone present. 'Why don't we settle this with a proper contest? Let our abilities do the talking.'"

3458665746.m_KeyValue: ""'Now, now, let's not point fingers at each other.' The golden-haired woman clapped her hands to quiet everyone down. 'After all, none of us came here today to fight, did we?'""

3458665747.m_KeyValue: ""Moments later, Acappella and the golden-haired woman appeared in the distance, glancing around as if searching for something.""

3458665749.m_KeyValue: ""'Hmph, dummy Empousa doesn't even realize she's been tricked.'""

3458665750.m_KeyValue: ""'One point...' Lamia pondered with her hand on her chin. 'Hmph, I get it. As long as we keep the ball from touching the ground, we can have multiple exchanges even in a single point.'""

3458665751.m_KeyValue: ""'It's the court boundaries, dummy Empousa.' Lamia stared intently at the lines Acappella had casually drawn. 'So this is the power of a Bell Ringer...'""

3458665752.m_KeyValue: ""Fishing does sound a bit dull, even if it was Commander's idea...' Acappella tilted her head in thought. 'Ah! I know—let's play ball!'""

3458668881.m_KeyValue: ""'Still… same dive or not, yours lacked my signature flair.'""

3458668882.m_KeyValue: ""Would it be the ever-fiery Agares who claimed victory? Or would Noah, the unchanging protagonist, seize first place once again? The answer lay just ahead.""

3458668883.m_KeyValue: ""'I swam with the little fish, drifted with the seaweed. My soul felt boundless—until it touched the shore of another.'""

3458668884.m_KeyValue: ""'My, my. You're looking pretty rough today, Noah.' Agares crouched lazily by the shore, his grin full of mischief.""

3458668885.m_KeyValue: ""Moonlight poured down, casting all three in soft silver. Their shadows stretched long across the sand—easy, unburdened.""

3458668887.m_KeyValue: ""Wait—Noah had resurfaced! He had caught up to Agares, and now the two were neck and neck!""

3458668888.m_KeyValue: ""Agares threw an arm over Noah's shoulder. 'Well now, Noah… who'd have thought that we'd both be the loser?'""

3458671053.m_KeyValue: ""'You mean...' Empousa turned to look at Lamia, who wore the same shocked expression. 'We're going to be rich...?'""

3458671054.m_KeyValue: ""'...Otherwise, even if you manage to collect the debt by force, the money will somehow get blown into the sea by a mysterious wind.""

3458671057.m_KeyValue: ""'...I don't need a dummy like Empousa to tell me that!' As she spoke, Lamia clasped her hands together and slammed them down with tremendous force! The ball shot toward the opposite court with a fierce whistle!""

3458671059.m_KeyValue: ""'Well, it doesn't matter anyway.' Acappella turned and walked away. 'The Commander probably did that on purpose anyway.'""

3458671060.m_KeyValue: ""'That thing Cain mentioned...' Lamia scanned the surroundings. 'It should be somewhere around here, right?'""

3458671061.m_KeyValue: ""'...Rules don't limit how we touch the ball,' Lamia said with a sly smile. ' Or hit it, which means—'""

3458671062.m_KeyValue: ""'The rules didn't say anything about using external forces, did they?' Acappella gently tapped upward, sending the fish-skin ball floating into the air. 'Commander—'""

3458671063.m_KeyValue: ""As soon as Empousa's words faded, a sea of crimson flowers burst forth from the ground. The blossoms grew rapidly, their vines intertwining to form an intricate net.""

3458671064.m_KeyValue: ""'So... that counts as one touch, doesn't it?' Acappella 'kindly' reminded the team across the net. 'Only two chances left! Better make them count!'""

3462039791.m_KeyValue: ""What are your thoughts on 'collecting Future Artifacts highly sought after by various factions, despite significant risks'?""

3462041969.m_KeyValue: "What are your thoughts on arranging for vassals to infiltrate the territories of other Kingdoms?"

3462045040.m_KeyValue: "What are your thoughts on 'reducing the scope of authority of our elders'?"

3464947065.m_KeyValue: ""The blonde youth drifted off mid-sentence. His companion, however, laid wide awake, his mind a tempest of thoughts.""

3474940660.m_KeyValue:
""Bella awoke from unconsciousness, pain stabbing through every inch of her body.
She remembered her illness flaring again, being carried to bed by servants, and then...
'Where am I?'
She looked around. Her left leg was missing, but the bandages were clean and tight. In the water tank beside her floated siren corpses, their bodies mutilated beyond recognition.
'Was I kidnapped? Them too? Who would do this…?'
Grabbing a stick for balance, Bella limped toward the exit, hopping on one leg. She knew where to find allies who would help her uncover the truth.
'I have to reach the meeting point. I must warn Lorelei—someone is hunting the sirens!'
'I can still run...'""

3531331928.m_KeyValue: ""I must strongly disagree. These so-called 'vassals' are manufactured from mere drops of blood, their Bloodline diluted. How can they be compared to vassals born through the proper Embrace ritual? Granting them the most basic rights should suffice.""

3531332025.m_KeyValue: ""You may not know, but hundreds of years ago, the family sent vassals to retrieve these 'Future Artifacts.' They not only failed to find any trace of treasure but also wasted vast resources. This expedition will likely lead to a direct confrontation with the Church. In my opinion, we should abandon this endeavor.""

3531332060.m_KeyValue: ""Too young, too imprudent. Experimenting with alchemical formulas they barely comprehend... One misstep and they'll face the dire consequences of their own folly.""

In 1235, three vassals were sent aboard the 'Virgin Lady' to explore the southwestern Sea of Medimar in search of the Other Side. They were never heard from again.""

3531332157.m_KeyValue: ""Wait, wait! Those mining sites are guarded by clergy members with formidable Blood Power! Going there rashly will surely lead to direct conflict. Our limited number of vassals will be captured before we can even uncover the truth. I say we should abandon this plan!""

3531332223.m_KeyValue: ""Are you completely oblivious to the risks? Our family has been studying alchemy for ages, and we still haven't grasped its full nature.""

3531332258.m_KeyValue: ""On the contrary! It is precisely because our family's Bloodline is declining that we must ensure the purity of our vassals' lineage! In my opinion, elders should have absolute authority over newly created Bloodborn.""

3531332355.m_KeyValue: "Recreating vassals and preparing for the 'return to the moon' are all thanks to Cain's efforts. You probably have no idea how much he has contributed to reviving the Bathory family's bloodline."

Perhaps it's because the world is too noisy that Acappella chose to join the Choir, using music to drown out the sorrowful sounds in her heart.""

3592805586.m_KeyValue: ""Perhaps this act of goodwill is what connects us in the future. As heir to the Alita family, Aiona—like her two cherished friends—had followed the path laid out for her since childhood. Bound by duty to their noble bloodlines, they all carried unspoken doubts, yet none dared to defy the fate carved for them. They placed their lives in each other's hands, believing their mutual faith would protect them from the Black Blood's creeping corruption, the resurgence of the Apocalypse, the fury of the Cataclysm, and even threats unforeseen by the Church. That is, until that mission—when Aiona glimpsed the future she was destined to embrace. To preserve the possibility of reunion with her old friends—even if they met again under different identities—she chose to walk the one path of no return among countless diverging roads.""

3595497007.m_KeyValue: ""Long weary of gold and jewels, the crowned nobles have now turned to seek out rare specimens to showcase their knowledge and curiosity.
